{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XvThfVoyFwTr2tJmnTdJT9","type":"tool_result","content":"hypotheses/h-stepml/problem.md:486:11. **Per-model TTFT additive corrections** — simple per-model constants (16-61ms) reduce TTFT from 67.6% to 9.4%\nhypotheses/h-stepml/problem.md:508:| Post-hoc corrections on CMA-ES results | TTFT additive corrections conflict with CMA-ES-optimized coefficients (+2.1pp worse) | R3 |\nhypotheses/h-stepml/problem.md:545:| H3: Additive TTFT corrections | -5pp E2E | +2.1pp worse; TTFT 9.4% | Refuted for E2E |\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/research.md:31:3. **TTFT additive corrections (from R3 H3):** Per-model TTFT corrections (16–61ms) are applied *within the objective evaluation*, not post-hoc. CMA-ES sees the corrected E2E and optimizes around it, avoiding the R3 H3 double-counting issue.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/research.md:45:All 5 methods via CMA-ES parameter tuning: StepTime (regime coefficients + overhead floor), QueueingTime (TTFT corrections), OutputTokenProcessingTime, SchedulingProcessingTime, PreemptionProcessingTime.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/research.md:98:6. **Combine with TTFT additive corrections:** Apply per-model TTFT corrections from R3 H3 (16–61ms) directly in the artifact's QueueingTime model.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/research.md:110:StepTime (primary — cycle time regression), QueueingTime (TTFT corrections). OutputTokenProcessingTime set to 0 (absorbed into cycle time model). SchedulingProcessingTime and PreemptionProcessingTime remain 0 (absorbed into intercept).\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/research.md:156:   - Apply TTFT additive corrections from R3 H3\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/research.md:181:- QueueingTime: TTFT additive corrections (Stage 1) + fine-tuning (Stage 2)\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/idea-1-constrained-cmaes/HYPOTHESIS.md:15:3. **Integrated TTFT corrections** (from R3 H3) applied during optimization rather than post-hoc\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/idea-1-constrained-cmaes/HYPOTHESIS.md:35:4. Apply TTFT additive corrections (per-model, from R3 H3) inside the objective evaluation loop\nhypotheses/h-stepml/research.md:31:3. **TTFT additive corrections (from R3 H3):** Per-model TTFT corrections (16–61ms) are applied *within the objective evaluation*, not post-hoc. CMA-ES sees the corrected E2E and optimizes around it, avoiding the R3 H3 double-counting issue.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/research.md:45:All 5 methods via CMA-ES parameter tuning: StepTime (regime coefficients + overhead floor), QueueingTime (TTFT corrections), OutputTokenProcessingTime, SchedulingProcessingTime, PreemptionProcessingTime.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/research.md:98:6. **Combine with TTFT additive corrections:** Apply per-model TTFT corrections from R3 H3 (16–61ms) directly in the artifact's QueueingTime model.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/research.md:110:StepTime (primary — cycle time regression), QueueingTime (TTFT corrections). OutputTokenProcessingTime set to 0 (absorbed into cycle time model). SchedulingProcessingTime and PreemptionProcessingTime remain 0 (absorbed into intercept).\nhypotheses/h-stepml/research.md:156:   - Apply TTFT additive corrections from R3 H3\nhypotheses/h-stepml/research.md:181:- QueueingTime: TTFT additive corrections (Stage 1) + fine-tuning (Stage 2)\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/idea-2-cycle-time-regression/HYPOTHESIS.md:57:   - TTFT correction from R3 H3 in QueueingTime\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/idea-3-hybrid-calibration/HYPOTHESIS.md:29:**Claim:** Cycle-time regression (from Idea 2) combined with TTFT additive corrections produces a base model with **mean E2E < 30%** and **mean ITL < 20%** across 10 experiments.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/idea-3-hybrid-calibration/HYPOTHESIS.md:35:2. Apply per-model TTFT additive corrections from R3 H3 (16–61ms) to QueueingTime\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/idea-3-hybrid-calibration/HYPOTHESIS.md:41:**Note:** If Idea 2 H2 already reports BLIS E2E results, H1 here simply adds TTFT corrections. The key