{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PQmQK5q4QurEuZAtE9y4Ue","type":"tool_result","content":"   208→\n   209→## Baseline Results (WP0)\n   210→\n   211→### BLIS E2E Validation — Per-Model Linear Regression (THE NUMBER TO BEAT)\n   212→\n   213→Per-model+TP linear regression (one regression per model group, pooling all workloads):\n   214→- **Mean E2E error: 115.0%** (0/12 experiments below 10% target)\n   215→- Mean TTFT error: 102.9%\n   216→- Mean ITL error: 134.6%\n   217→- **R4 gate: PASSED** — blackbox is clearly insufficient, research is justified\n   218→\n   219→Per-model training coefficients (note negative intercepts producing invalid predictions):\n   220→\n   221→| Model+TP | beta0 | beta1 | beta2 | Train MAPE | Train r |\n   222→|----------|-------|-------|-------|------------|---------|\n   223→| CodeLlama-34B tp=2 | -5525 | 0.421 | 215.1 | 675.8% | 0.918 |\n   224→| Llama-2-70B tp=4 | -2633 | 1.306 | 106.4 | 199.2% | 0.934 |\n   225→| Llama-2-7B tp=1 | 992 | 3.403 | 7.031 | 610.3% | 0.359 |\n   226→| Mixtral-8x7B tp=2 | -8035 | 0.000 | 249.3 | 965.6% | 0.778 |\n   227→\n   228→Per-experiment BLIS E2E errors:\n   229→\n   230→| Experiment | E2E Error | TTFT Error | ITL Error |\n   231→|---|---|---|---|\n   232→| llama-2-7b-tp1-codegen | 86.2% | 88.0% | 72.3% |\n   233→| llama-2-7b-tp1-roleplay | 86.1% | 85.9% | 72.2% |\n   234→| llama-2-7b-tp1-general | 90.8% | 92.0% | 81.6% |\n   235→| llama-2-70b-tp4-general | 111.8% | 102.0% | 124.1% |\n   236→| llama-2-70b-tp4-codegen | 113.6% | 103.6% | 127.5% |\n   237→| llama-2-70b-tp4-roleplay | 113.9% | 103.4% | 128.2% |\n   238→| mixtral-8x7b-tp2-codegen | 141.3% | 113.7% | 183.5% |\n   239→| mixtral-8x7b-tp2-general | 138.5% | 111.7% | 177.9% |\n   240→| mixtral-8x7b-tp2-roleplay | 141.9% | 113.3% | 184.7% |\n   241→| codellama-34b-tp2-general | 132.3% | 110.3% | 165.3% |\n   242→| codellama-34b-tp2-codegen | 135.4% | 111.7% | 171.5% |\n   243→| codellama-34b-tp2-roleplay | 136.5% | 111.5% | 173.7% |\n   244→\n   245→### BLIS E2E Validation — Roofline (Informational Only)\n   246→\n   247→The analytical roofline model (zero calibration, FLOPs/bandwidth-based):\n   248→- **Mean E2E error: 4816%** (10/16 completed, 6 timed out at 300s)\n   249→- Massively overestimates step time, causing request starvation\n   250→- Only Mixtral codegen/roleplay were within 35% (GEMM-dominated workloads)\n   251→- The roofline model is informational only — ideas MUST NOT use roofline as input\n   252→\n   253→### Component Error Attribution (BC-0-6)\n   254→\n   255→StepTime dominates E2E error in all 12 experiments. With alpha=[0,0,0] (blackbox defaults):\n   256→- Queueing contribution: 0% (alpha coefficients are zero)\n   257→- Output processing: 0% (alpha2 is zero)\n   258→- Scheduling: 0 (returns 0)\n   259→- Preemption: 0 (returns 0)\n   260→- **Step time: 100% of modeled error**. Per-step MAPE ranges from 28.5% to 1287% (codegen, high batch variance)\n   261→\n   262→**Recommendation:** All improvement effort should focus on StepTime prediction. Any non-zero contribution to queueing/scheduling/preemption is additive benefit since the blackbox currently returns 0 for all of them.\n   263→\n   264→### Round 1 Per-Step Baselines (Historical Reference)\n   265→\n   266→Round 1 tested per-step MAPE only (no BLIS E2E validation):\n   267→- **Per-experiment XGBoost (30 features):** 34.0% avg MAPE — 2x better than blackbox (70.4%)\n   268→- **Global blackbox:** 670% MAPE — catastrophic failure across model scales\n   269→- **Key insight:** Per-step MAPE ≠ E2E error. The 34% per-step MAPE was never validated through BLIS.\n   270→\n   271→### Validation Gate Summary\n   272→\n   273→| Gate | Status | Detail |\n   274→|------|--------|--------|\n   275→| R1 (ProgressIndex as KV proxy) | FLAGGED | Pearson r ≈ 0 between total_tokens and E2E time; ProgressIndex is valid for KV cache length but not for E2E prediction. Lifecycle KV extractor available as fallback. |\n   276→| R2 (Sampling bias) | PASS | CV=0.44, max/min ratio=4.2, random sampling confirmed (~10% rate) |\n   277→| R4 (Blackbox sufficient?) | PASS | 115% E2E mean error — clearly beatable |\n   278→\n   279→## Evaluation Framework\n   280→\n   281→### Primary Metric\n   282→\n   283→**Workload-level E2E mean error < 10%** on each of the 12 experiments individually. For each experiment:\n   284→```\n   285→predicted_mean_e2e = mean over requests of (sum of predicted step times along request's path)\n   286→observed_mean_e2e  = mean over requests of (observed request-level E2E latency)\n   287→E2E_mean_error     = |predicted_mean_e2e - observed_mean_e2e| / observed_mean_e2e\n   288→```\n   289→\n   290→### All Metrics (ordered by priority)\n   291→\n   292→| Priority | Metric | Target |\n   293→|----------|--------|--------|\n   294→| P1 | Workload-level E2E mean error | < 10% per experiment |\n   295→| P1 | Per-step MAPE, Pearson r | Diagnostic (no hard target) |\n   296→| **P2** | **Generalization: model (LOMO)** | **LOMO MAPE < 80% per fold** |\n   297→| **P2** | **Generalization: workload (LOWO)** | **LOWO MAPE < 50% per fold** |\n   298→| **P2** | **Generalization: vLLM args sensitivity** | **Qualitative robustness analysis per idea** |\n   299→| P2 | TTFT mean fidelity | < 15% per experiment |\n   300→| P2 | ITL mean fidelity | < 15% per experiment |\n   301→| P3 | Tail behavior (p99) | No ranking inversions vs baseline |\n   302→| P3 | Ease of use, retraining story, reproducibility | Qualitative |\n   303→| P4 | Hardware generalization (H100 → A100) | Informational |\n   304→| P5 | Quantization transferability | Informational |\n   305→\n   306→> **Generalization is P2, not optional.** An idea that achieves <10% E2E but fails LOMO/LOWO/vLLM-args analysis is **not a viable winner** — it would be useless in production where new models, workloads, and vLLM configurations are deployed routinely. Reviewers MUST evaluate generalization with the same rigor as accuracy.\n   307→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RVuaHJFo1hExchGpHGTkix","session_id":"e652145f-d03b-4eb5-bbf8-d7db257fe10a","uuid":"cc834453-0a9e-47f4-9872-c6c9111a56ba"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GFBfXV5s92kBZUiAK5Equg","type":"tool_result","content":"hypotheses/h-stepml/round1/idea-3-evolutionary-synthesis/h2-model/HYPOTHESIS.md:14:After 500 generations x 5 independent runs, the best evolved function achieves >15% E2E mean error on more than 4 experiments. The extended budget (500 generations vs. 100 in h1) and relaxed threshold (15% vs. 10%) account for the increased difficulty of E2E optimization (where per-step errors propagate through the simulation). If evolution cannot reach 15% with analytical components as inputs, the combination of evolutionary search + analytical decomposition does not synergize.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/problem.md:214:- **Mean E2E error: 115.0%** (0/12 experiments below 10% target)\nhypotheses/h-stepml/problem.md:513:Round 3 tested 3 ideas on 10 experiments (5 models × 3 workloads). **Key achievement: 427.8% → 15.1% mean E2E (28.3x improvement)** via two advances: trace replay eliminated workload-spec errors, CMA-ES found per-model coefficient settings. Full details: `round3/FINDINGS_ROUND3.md`.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/run_research_loop.sh:404:            # Look for patterns like \"X% mean E2E\" or \"mean E2E error: X%\" or \"E2E: X%\"\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round1/idea-1-tree-ensemble/h2-model/HYPOTHESIS.md:33:**Error propagation analysis:** Per-step prediction errors may cancel (symmetric errors around zero) or compound (systematic bias) when aggregated into workload-level E2E mean. This experiment explicitly measures both per-step MAPE and workload-level E2E mean error to characterize the propagation relationship.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round1/DECISION_GATE.md:11:Three research ideas were explored to replace BLIS's blackbox latency model (3-coefficient linear regression on `prefill_tokens` and `decode_tokens`) with a data-driven step-time predictor achieving <10% workload-level E2E mean error:\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round1/DECISION_GATE.md:71:**Gap:** Workload-level E2E mean error was not computed because that requires running BLIS simulation with the trained model as the latency backend. Per-step MAPE is a diagnostic, not the primary metric. E2E mean error could be better (if per-step errors cancel) or worse (if they compound) than per-step MAPE.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round1/DECISION_GATE.md:79:| Outperforms blackbox on E2E, TTFT, ITL | All three | Not tested | UNKNOWN |\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round1/DECISION_GATE.md:169:1. **Ship as opt-in** (`--stepml` flag), not as the default. The blackbox model remains default until E2E validation completes.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round1/research.md:21:**The goal is to replace this blackbox model with a data-driven alternative achieving <10% workload-level E2E mean error across all 16 experiments, while the winning model must integrate back into BLIS as a Go LatencyModel implementation.**\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round1/research.md:863:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round1/research.md:1340:3. **Quality metric**: Negative of mean E2E error across all 16 experiments (higher is better).\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round1/research.md:1515:- Stop after 1000 generations or when the best program's mean E2E error has not improved by >0.5% for 200 consecutive generations.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/shared/baselines.py:179:    This means the blackbox model is already performing well at the E2E level,\nhypotheses/h-stepml/shared/baselines.py:183:        blackbox_e2e_mean_error: The blackbox baseline's E2E mean error as a percentage.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/shared/baselines.py:195:            f\"R4 gate FLAGGED: blackbox E2E mean error = {e2e_error:.1f}% \"\nhypotheses/h-stepml/shared/baselines.py:201:            f\"R4 gate passed: blackbox E2E mean error = {e2e_error:.1f}% \"\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round1/round1_FINDINGS_SUMMARY.md:11:Replace BLIS's 3-coefficient blackbox latency model (`step_time = beta0 + beta1*prefill_tokens + beta2*decode_tokens`) with a data-driven predictor achieving **<10% workload-level E2E mean error** across 16 experiments (4 models × 4 workloads, H100 GPUs). The winning model must integrate into BLIS as a Go `LatencyModel` implementation.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round1/round1_FINDINGS_SUMMARY.md:306:The primary metric is workload-level E2E mean error (not per-step MAPE). Per-step errors may cancel in aggregate. The 34% per-step MAPE might translate to <10% E2E mean error if errors are symmetric. This was NOT tested in Round 1. Round 2 should include BLIS E2E validation.\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:13:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:15:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:16:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:34:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:35:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:36:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:80:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:81:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:88:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:89:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:90:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:91:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:92:[Omitted long matching line]\nhypotheses/h-stepml/round4/phase1_wp1_wp2.log:93:[Omitted long matching line]"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RVuaHJFo1hExchGpHGTkix","session_id":"e652145f-d03b-4eb5-bbf8-d7db257fe10a","uuid":"eeea5f83-a400-4d85-8f99-91d2cd34fd29"}
