{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_01Vh2LNbEZ9wccNa87HT5h7D","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All dependencies are available. Now I have a complete understanding of the context. Let me create the experiment infrastructure for Idea 3.\n\n`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\nThis hybrid calibration approach combines two orthogonal advances from R3:\n1. **Cycle-time regression** (Idea 2) models the *actual* step cycle time (inter-token interval) instead of just GPU compute time, naturally absorbing the overhead floor\n2. **Constrained CMA-ES** (Idea 1) performs black-box optimization of simulation parameters\n\nThe key insight is that CMA-ES in R3 had to make *large* distortions (e.g., inflating output_token_processing_time 0→1,899μs) because the base model was badly miscalibrated. If Stage 1 provides a well-calibrated base, Stage 2 CMA-ES only needs *small* residual corrections — the E2E↔ITL tradeoff softens.\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e652145f-d03b-4eb5-bbf8-d7db257fe10a","uuid":"1dfe71a4-216d-4e49-a6f7-a10375052698"}
