{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_01VVqpA6YEsQ3Wuzqn4y61Qm","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\nThe cycle time from `ts_start_ns` differences is ~100-300x larger than `step.duration_us` because step.ts_start_ns measures the **wall-clock time between step starts**, which includes:\n- GPU compute (step.duration_us) \n- CPU scheduling overhead\n- **Idle time** between steps (when the system is waiting for new requests)\n\nThe \"cycle time\" we want is the **inter-token interval (ITI)** from lifecycle data — the time between consecutive output tokens. This captures compute + overhead but NOT idle time. I need to use the lifecycle approach instead.\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\n\nThe ts_start_ns difference approach produces enormous cycle times because it includes idle time. I need to use the lifecycle ITI approach or a different strategy. Let me use a hybrid: compute the overhead from ITL data directly and apply it as a multiplier to step.duration_us."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e652145f-d03b-4eb5-bbf8-d7db257fe10a","uuid":"61eef5fe-723f-477f-83a6-ae7a5f858225"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_01VVqpA6YEsQ3Wuzqn4y61Qm","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01RGmKvSngN3mGp81QfrkEPf","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/stepml-worktrees/round4-idea-3-hybrid-calibration/hypotheses/h-stepml/round4/idea-3-hybrid-calibration/h1-principled-base/run.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"H1: Stage 1 Principled Base — Overhead-Scaled Step Time + TTFT Corrections.\n\nKey insight from R3: BLIS simulates a \"faster universe\" (~40% of real time).\nThe root cause is that step.duration_us measures only GPU forward-pass time,\nwhile real step cycle time includes CPU scheduling overhead, CUDA sync, and\nmemory management. The overhead floor (max(overhead, compute)) is the right\nmechanism but needs calibration from lifecycle data.\n\nThis script:\n1. Computes per-model median ITL from lifecycle data (the true step cycle time)\n2. Computes per-model median step.duration_us (GPU-only time)\n3. Derives overhead_multiplier = median_ITL / median_duration (typically ~2-3x)\n4. Trains per-model regime regression on SCALED step times (duration * multiplier)\n5. Applies TTFT additive corrections from lifecycle data\n6. Exports StepML artifacts and runs BLIS validation\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport os\nimport sys\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import Ridge\n\n# Add shared infrastructure to path\n_SCRIPT_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))\n_IDEA_DIR = os.path.dirname(_SCRIPT_DIR)\n_SHARED_DIR = os.path.join(_IDEA_DIR, \"..\", \"..\", \"shared\")\nsys.path.insert(0, _SHARED_DIR)\n\nfrom data_loader import (\n    load_all_experiments,\n    load_lifecycle_data,\n    parse_experiment_metadata,\n    DEFAULT_DATA_ROOT,\n)\nfrom evaluation import compute_mape\nfrom validate_blis import DEFAULT_BINARY\n\nOUTPUT_DIR = os.path.join(_SCRIPT_DIR, \"output\")\nos.makedirs(OUTPUT_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 1: Compute per-model ITL from lifecycle data\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef compute_per_model_itl(data_root: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Compute per-model median inter-token latency from lifecycle data.\n\n    ITL = median of (output_token_times[i+1] - output_token_times[i]) for all\n    requests in all experiments for each model. This is the true step cycle time\n    as seen by the client (GPU compute + CPU overhead + CUDA sync).\n    \"\"\"\n    model_itls = {}  # {model: [itl_values]}\n\n    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(data_root)):\n        dirpath = os.path.join(data_root, dirname)\n        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n            continue\n        lifecycle_path = os.path.join(\n            dirpath, \"results\", \"per_request_lifecycle_metrics.json\"\n        )\n        if not os.path.isfile(lifecycle_path):\n            continue\n\n        meta = parse_experiment_metadata(dirname)\n        model = meta[\"model\"]\n\n        try:\n            lifecycle_df = load_lifecycle_data(dirpath)\n        except Exception:\n            continue\n\n        itls = []\n        for _, row in lifecycle_df.iterrows():\n            times = row.get(\"output_token_times\", [])\n            if not times or len(times) < 2:\n                continue\n            for i in range(1, len(times)):\n                iti_s = times[i] - times[i - 1]\n                if iti_s > 0:\n                    itls.append(iti_s * 1_000_000)  # convert to us\n\n        if itls:\n            model_itls.setdefault(model, []).extend(itls)\n\n    result = {}\n    for model, itls in model_itls.items():\n        arr = np.array(itls)\n        result[model] = {\n            \"median_itl_us\": float(np.median(arr)),\n            \"mean_itl_us\": float(np.mean(arr)),\n            \"p10_itl_us\": float(np.percentile(arr, 10)),\n            \"p90_itl_us\": float(np.percentile(arr, 90)),\n            \"n_tokens\": len(arr),\n        }\n        print(\n            f\"  {model}: median_ITL={result[model]['median_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"\n            f\"mean_ITL={result[model]['mean_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"\n            f\"p10={result[model]['p10_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"\n            f\"p90={result[model]['p90_itl_us']:.0f}us, n={len(arr)}\"\n        )\n\n    return result\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 2: Compute overhead multiplier per model\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef compute_overhead_multipliers(\n    step_df: pd.DataFrame, itl_data: dict\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Compute per-model overhead multiplier = median_ITL / median_step_duration.\n\n    This captures the ratio of real cycle time (ITL) to GPU-only time (duration).\n    \"\"\"\n    multipliers = {}\n    for model in sorted(step_df[\"model\"].unique()):\n        mdf = step_df[step_df[\"model\"] == model]\n        dur = mdf[\"step.duration_us\"].dropna()\n        if len(dur) == 0:\n            continue\n\n        median_dur = float(dur.median())\n        itl_info = itl_data.get(model)\n        if itl_info is None:\n            # Try normalized name\n            for k, v in itl_data.items():\n                if k.replace(\"-hf\", \"\") == model.replace(\"-hf\", \"\"):\n                    itl_info = v\n                    break\n\n        if itl_info is None:\n            print(f\"  {model}: no ITL data, using 2.0x default multiplier\")\n            multipliers[model] = {\n                \"multiplier\": 2.0,\n                \"median_dur_us\": median_dur,\n                \"median_itl_us\": median_dur * 2.0,\n            }\n            continue\n\n        median_itl = itl_info[\"median_itl_us\"]\n        mult = median_itl / median_dur if median_dur > 0 else 2.0\n\n        # Clamp to reasonable range [1.2, 10.0]\n        mult = max(1.2, min(10.0, mult))\n\n        multipliers[model] = {\n            \"multiplier\": float(mult),\n            \"median_dur_us\": float(median_dur),\n            \"median_itl_us\": float(median_itl),\n        }\n        print(\n            f\"  {model}: multiplier={mult:.2f}x \"\n            f\"(median_ITL={median_itl:.0f}us / median_dur={median_dur:.0f}us)\"\n        )\n\n    return multipliers\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 3: Train per-model regression on overhead-scaled step times\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef train_per_model_regression(\n    step_df: pd.DataFrame, multipliers: dict\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Train per-model regime regression on overhead-scaled step times.\n\n    target = step.duration_us * overhead_multiplier (the estimated cycle time)\n    features = [scheduled_tokens, num_decode_reqs]\n    \"\"\"\n    models = {}\n\n    for model_name in sorted(step_df[\"model\"].unique()):\n        mdf = step_df[step_df[\"model\"] == model_name].copy()\n        mult_info = multipliers.get(model_name, {\"multiplier\": 2.0})\n        mult = mult_info[\"multiplier\"]\n\n        # Compute scaled target\n        mdf = mdf.dropna(subset=[\"step.duration_us\"])\n        mdf[\"scaled_duration_us\"] = mdf[\"step.duration_us\"].astype(float) * mult\n\n        # Feature columns\n        if \"batch.scheduled_tokens\" in mdf.columns:\n            mdf[\"new_tokens\"] = mdf[\"batch.scheduled_tokens\"].astype(float)\n        else:\n            mdf[\"new_tokens\"] = (\n                mdf.get(\"batch.prefill_tokens\", pd.Series(0, index=mdf.index)).astype(float)\n                + mdf.get(\"batch.decode_tokens\", pd.Series(0, index=mdf.index)).astype(float)\n            )\n\n        mdf[\"n_decode_reqs\"] = mdf.get(\n            \"batch.num_decode_reqs\", pd.Series(0, index=mdf.index)\n        ).astype(float)\n\n        # Regime separation\n        if \"batch.prefill_tokens\" in mdf.columns:\n            decode_only = mdf[mdf[\"batch.prefill_tokens\"] == 0]\n            mixed = mdf[mdf[\"batch.prefill_tokens\"] > 0]\n        else:\n            decode_only = mdf\n            mixed = mdf.iloc[0:0]\n\n        regimes = {\"multiplier\": mult}\n\n        # Train decode-only\n        if len(decode_only) >= 10:\n            X = decode_only[[\"new_tokens\", \"n_decode_reqs\"]].values\n            y = decode_only[\"scaled_duration_us\"].values\n            reg = Ridge(alpha=10.0)\n            reg.fit(X, y)\n            pred = reg.predict(X)\n            mape = compute_mape(pred, y)\n            regimes[\"decode_only\"] = {\n                \"intercept\": float(reg.intercept_),\n                \"coeff_new_tokens\": float(reg.coef_[0]),\n                \"coeff_n_decode_reqs\": float(reg.coef_[1]),\n                \"mape\": mape,\n                \"n\": len(decode_only),\n                \"mean_target\": float(y.mean()),\n            }\n            print(\n                f\"  {model_name} decode-only: intercept={reg.intercept_:.0f}, \"\n                f\"b_tokens={reg.coef_[0]:.2f}, b_reqs={reg.coef_[1]:.2f}, \"\n                f\"MAPE={mape:.1f}%, n={len(decode_only)}\"\n            )\n\n        # Train mixed\n        if len(mixed) >= 10:\n            X = mixed[[\"new_tokens\", \"n_decode_reqs\"]].values\n            y = mixed[\"scaled_duration_us\"].values\n            reg = Ridge(alpha=10.0)\n            reg.fit(X, y)\n            pred = reg.predict(X)\n            mape = compute_mape(pred, y)\n            regimes[\"mixed\"] = {\n                \"intercept\": float(reg.intercept_),\n                \"coeff_new_tokens\": float(reg.coef_[0]),\n                \"coeff_n_decode_reqs\": float(reg.coef_[1]),\n                \"mape\": mape,\n                \"n\": len(mixed),\n                \"mean_target\": float(y.mean()),\n            }\n            print(\n                f\"  {model_name} mixed:       intercept={reg.intercept_:.0f}, \"\n                f\"b_tokens={reg.coef_[0]:.2f}, b_reqs={reg.coef_[1]:.2f}, \"\n                f\"MAPE={mape:.1f}%, n={len(mixed)}\"\n            )\n\n        # Global\n        X = mdf[[\"new_tokens\", \"n_decode_reqs\"]].values\n        y = mdf[\"scaled_duration_us\"].values\n        reg = Ridge(alpha=10.0)\n        reg.fit(X, y)\n        pred = reg.predict(X)\n        mape = compute_mape(pred, y)\n        regimes[\"global\"] = {\n            \"intercept\": float(reg.intercept_),\n            \"coeff_new_tokens\": float(reg.coef_[0]),\n            \"coeff_n_decode_reqs\": float(reg.coef_[1]),\n            \"mape\": mape,\n            \"n\": len(mdf),\n            \"mean_target\": float(y.mean()),\n        }\n\n        models[model_name] = regimes\n\n    return models\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 4: TTFT corrections from lifecycle data\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef estimate_ttft_corrections(data_root: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Per-model TTFT correction = observed mean TTFT from lifecycle data.\"\"\"\n    corrections = {}\n    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(data_root)):\n        dirpath = os.path.join(data_root, dirname)\n        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n            continue\n        lifecycle_path = os.path.join(\n            dirpath, \"results\", \"per_request_lifecycle_metrics.json\"\n        )\n        if not os.path.isfile(lifecycle_path):\n            continue\n\n        meta = parse_experiment_metadata(dirname)\n        model = meta[\"model\"]\n\n        try:\n            lifecycle_df = load_lifecycle_data(dirpath)\n        except Exception:\n            continue\n\n        ttft_values = []\n        for _, row in lifecycle_df.iterrows():\n            times = row.get(\"output_token_times\", [])\n            start = row.get(\"start_time\", 0)\n            if times and len(times) > 0 and start > 0:\n                ttft_s = times[0] - start\n                if ttft_s > 0:\n                    ttft_values.append(ttft_s)\n\n        if ttft_values:\n            corrections.setdefault(model, []).extend(ttft_values)\n\n    result = {}\n    for model, values in corrections.items():\n        mean_ttft_us = float(np.mean(values)) * 1_000_000\n        result[model] = mean_ttft_us\n        print(f\"  TTFT correction for {model}: {mean_ttft_us:.0f}us ({mean_ttft_us/1000:.1f}ms)\")\n\n    return result\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 5: Export StepML artifacts\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef export_stepml_artifact(\n    model_name: str, regimes: dict, ttft_correction_us: float, output_path: str\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Export per-model StepML JSON artifact.\"\"\"\n    mult = regimes.get(\"multiplier\", 2.0)\n\n    # Use decode-only intercept as overhead floor\n    if \"decode_only\" in regimes:\n        d = regimes[\"decode_only\"]\n        overhead_us = max(d[\"intercept\"], 1000)\n    elif \"global\" in regimes:\n        overhead_us = max(regimes[\"global\"][\"intercept\"], 1000)\n    else:\n        overhead_us = 4000\n\n    step_time_regimes = []\n\n    if \"decode_only\" in regimes:\n        d = regimes[\"decode_only\"]\n        step_time_regimes.append(\n            {\n                \"name\": \"decode_only\",\n                \"condition\": {\"feature\": \"prefill_tokens\", \"op\": \"==\", \"value\": 0},\n                \"model\": {\n                    \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n                    \"intercept\": d[\"intercept\"],\n                    \"feature_coefficients\": {\n                        \"decode_tokens\": d[\"coeff_new_tokens\"],\n                        \"num_decode_reqs\": d[\"coeff_n_decode_reqs\"],\n                    },\n                },\n            }\n        )\n\n    if \"mixed\" in regimes:\n        m = regimes[\"mixed\"]\n        step_time_regimes.append(\n            {\n                \"name\": \"mixed\",\n                \"condition\": None,\n                \"model\": {\n                    \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n                    \"intercept\": m[\"intercept\"],\n                    \"feature_coefficients\": {\n                        \"scheduled_tokens\": m[\"coeff_new_tokens\"],\n                        \"num_decode_reqs\": m[\"coeff_n_decode_reqs\"],\n                    },\n                },\n            }\n        )\n\n    if not step_time_regimes:\n        g = regimes[\"global\"]\n        step_time_regimes.append(\n            {\n                \"name\": \"global\",\n                \"condition\": None,\n                \"model\": {\n                    \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n                    \"intercept\": g[\"intercept\"],\n                    \"feature_coefficients\": {\n                        \"scheduled_tokens\": g[\"coeff_new_tokens\"],\n                        \"num_decode_reqs\": g[\"coeff_n_decode_reqs\"],\n                    },\n                },\n            }\n        )\n\n    artifact = {\n        \"version\": 2,\n        \"step_time_regimes\": step_time_regimes,\n        \"step_overhead_us\": overhead_us,\n        \"output_token_processing_time_us\": 0,\n        \"scheduling_processing_time_us\": 0,\n        \"preemption_processing_time_us\": 0,\n    }\n\n    if ttft_correction_us > 0:\n        artifact[\"queueing_time\"] = {\n            \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n            \"intercept\": ttft_correction_us,\n            \"feature_coefficients\": {},\n        }\n\n    with open(output_path, \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump(artifact, f, indent=2)\n\n    print(\n        f\"  {model_name}: overhead={overhead_us:.0f}us, \"\n        f\"TTFT={ttft_correction_us:.0f}us, mult={mult:.2f}x\"\n    )\n    return artifact\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 6: BLIS validation\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef run_blis_validation_per_model(\n    data_root: str, artifacts: dict, output_csv: str\n) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    \"\"\"Run BLIS validation with per-model StepML artifacts.\"\"\"\n    from validate_blis import (\n        parse_experiment_dir,\n        load_ground_truth_metrics,\n        load_exp_config,\n        extract_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log,\n        extract_cpu_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log,\n        load_profile,\n        build_workload_spec,\n        run_blis,\n        compute_error,\n    )\n    import tempfile\n    import yaml\n\n    binary = DEFAULT_BINARY\n    if not os.path.isfile(binary):\n        import subprocess\n        repo_root = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(_SHARED_DIR, \"..\", \"..\", \"..\"))\n        subprocess.run([\"go\", \"build\", \"-o\", binary, \"main.go\"], cwd=repo_root, check=True)\n\n    results = []\n    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(data_root)):\n        dirpath = os.path.join(data_root, dirname)\n        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n            continue\n        summary_path = os.path.join(dirpath, \"results\", \"summary_lifecycle_metrics.json\")\n        if not os.path.isfile(summary_path):\n            continue\n\n        try:\n            meta = parse_experiment_dir(dirname)\n        except ValueError:\n            continue\n\n        model_name = meta[\"model\"]\n\n        # Find matching artifact\n        artifact_path = None\n        for art_model, art_path in artifacts.items():\n            if art_model == model_name:\n                artifact_path = art_path\n                break\n        if artifact_path is None:\n            for art_model, art_path in artifacts.items():\n                if art_model.replace(\"-hf\", \"\") == model_name.replace(\"-hf\", \"\"):\n                    artifact_path = art_path\n                    break\n        if artifact_path is None:\n            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"no_artifact\"})\n            continue\n\n        gt = load_ground_truth_metrics(dirpath)\n        exp_config = load_exp_config(dirpath)\n        total_kv_blocks = extract_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log(dirpath)\n        cpu_kv_blocks = extract_cpu_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log(dirpath)\n\n        if total_kv_blocks is None:\n            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"no_kv_blocks\"})\n            continue\n\n        try:\n            profile = load_profile(dirpath)\n        except Exception:\n            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"no_profile\"})\n            continue\n\n        workload_spec = build_workload_spec(profile, gt)\n\n        with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(mode=\"w\", suffix=\".yaml\", delete=False) as f:\n            yaml.dump(workload_spec, f, default_flow_style=False)\n            spec_path = f.name\n\n        with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(suffix=\".json\", delete=False) as f:\n            results_json_path = f.name\n\n        try:\n            blis_metrics = run_blis(\n                binary=binary,\n                workload_spec_path=spec_path,\n                exp_config=exp_config,\n                total_kv_blocks=total_kv_blocks,\n                alpha_coeffs=[0, 0, 0],\n                beta_coeffs=[0, 0, 0],\n                results_path=results_json_path,\n                stepml_model_path=artifact_path,\n                cpu_kv_blocks=cpu_kv_blocks,\n            )\n        finally:\n            os.unlink(spec_path)\n            if os.path.exists(results_json_path):\n                os.unlink(results_json_path)\n\n        if blis_metrics is None:\n            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"blis_failed\"})\n            continue\n\n        e2e_err = compute_error(blis_metrics[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], gt[\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n        ttft_err = compute_error(blis_metrics[\"ttft_mean_ms\"], gt[\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n        itl_err = compute_error(blis_metrics[\"itl_mean_ms\"], gt[\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n\n        print(f\"  {dirname}: E2E={e2e_err*100:.1f}%, TTFT={ttft_err*100:.1f}%, ITL={itl_err*100:.1f}%\")\n\n        results.append({\n            \"experiment\": dirname,\n            \"model\": model_name,\n            \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"],\n            \"tp\": meta[\"tp\"],\n            \"status\": \"ok\",\n            \"gt_e2e_ms\": gt[\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n            \"gt_ttft_ms\": gt[\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n            \"gt_itl_ms\": gt[\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n            \"blis_e2e_ms\": blis_metrics[\"e2e_mean_ms\"],\n            \"blis_ttft_ms\": blis_metrics[\"ttft_mean_ms\"],\n            \"blis_itl_ms\": blis_metrics[\"itl_mean_ms\"],\n            \"e2e_error\": e2e_err,\n            \"ttft_error\": ttft_err,\n            \"itl_error\": itl_err,\n            \"blis_completed\": blis_metrics[\"completed_requests\"],\n            \"gt_requests\": gt[\"num_requests\"],\n        })\n\n    df = pd.DataFrame(results)\n    df.to_csv(output_csv, index=False)\n    return df\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Main\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef main():\n    print(\"=\" * 70)\n    print(\"H1: Stage 1 Principled Base — Overhead-Scaled + TTFT Corrections\")\n    print(\"=\" * 70)\n\n    data_root = DEFAULT_DATA_ROOT\n\n    # Step 1: Compute ITL from lifecycle data\n    print(\"\\n--- Step 1: Per-model ITL from lifecycle data ---\")\n    itl_data = compute_per_model_itl(data_root)\n\n    # Step 2: Load step data and compute multipliers\n    print(\"\\n--- Step 2: Compute overhead multipliers ---\")\n    step_df = load_all_experiments(data_root)\n    multipliers = compute_overhead_multipliers(step_df, itl_data)\n\n    # Step 3: Train regression on scaled step times\n    print(\"\\n--- Step 3: Train per-model regression on scaled step times ---\")\n    models = train_per_model_regression(step_df, multipliers)\n\n    with open(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"regression_results.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump(models, f, indent=2, default=str)\n\n    # Step 4: TTFT corrections\n    print(\"\\n--- Step 4: TTFT corrections ---\")\n    ttft_corrections = estimate_ttft_corrections(data_root)\n\n    # Step 5: Export artifacts\n    print(\"\\n--- Step 5: Export StepML artifacts ---\")\n    artifact_dir = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"artifacts\")\n    os.makedirs(artifact_dir, exist_ok=True)\n\n    artifacts = {}\n    for model_name, regimes in models.items():\n        ttft_us = 0\n        for ttft_model, ttft_val in ttft_corrections.items():\n            if ttft_model == model_name or ttft_model.replace(\"-hf\", \"\") == model_name.replace(\"-hf\", \"\"):\n                ttft_us = ttft_val\n                break\n\n        artifact_path = os.path.join(artifact_dir, f\"{model_name}.json\")\n        export_stepml_artifact(model_name, regimes, ttft_us, artifact_path)\n        artifacts[model_name] = artifact_path\n\n    # Step 6: BLIS validation\n    print(\"\\n--- Step 6: BLIS validation ---\")\n    results_csv = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"blis_validation.csv\")\n    results_df = run_blis_validation_per_model(data_root, artifacts, results_csv)\n\n    # Summary\n    ok = results_df[results_df[\"status\"] == \"ok\"]\n    if len(ok) > 0:\n        mean_e2e = ok[\"e2e_error\"].mean() * 100\n        mean_ttft = ok[\"ttft_error\"].mean() * 100\n        mean_itl = ok[\"itl_error\"].mean() * 100\n\n        print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\n        print(\"STAGE 1 RESULTS SUMMARY\")\n        print(\"=\" * 70)\n        print(f\"Experiments: {len(ok)}\")\n        print(f\"Mean E2E:  {mean_e2e:.1f}% (target <30%)\")\n        print(f\"Mean TTFT: {mean_ttft:.1f}%\")\n        print(f\"Mean ITL:  {mean_itl:.1f}% (target <20%)\")\n        below_10 = (ok[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.10).sum()\n        print(f\"E2E < 10%: {below_10}/{len(ok)}\")\n\n        print(f\"\\n{'Experiment':<55} {'E2E%':>7} {'TTFT%':>7} {'ITL%':>7}\")\n        print(\"-\" * 80)\n        for _, row in ok.iterrows():\n            print(\n                f\"{row['experiment']:<55} {row['e2e_error']*100:>7.1f} \"\n                f\"{row['ttft_error']*100:>7.1f} {row['itl_error']*100:>7.1f}\"\n            )\n        print(\"-\" * 80)\n        print(f\"{'MEAN':<55} {mean_e2e:>7.1f} {mean_ttft:>7.1f} {mean_itl:>7.1f}\")\n\n        # Save summary\n        summary = {\n            \"mean_e2e_error\": mean_e2e,\n            \"mean_ttft_error\": mean_ttft,\n            \"mean_itl_error\": mean_itl,\n            \"n_experiments\": len(ok),\n            \"n_below_10_e2e\": int(below_10),\n            \"per_experiment\": ok[\n                [\"experiment\", \"model\", \"workload\", \"e2e_error\", \"ttft_error\", \"itl_error\",\n                 \"gt_e2e_ms\", \"blis_e2e_ms\", \"gt_itl_ms\", \"blis_itl_ms\"]\n            ].to_dict(\"records\"),\n            \"multipliers\": multipliers,\n            \"regression_results\": {k: {rk: rv for rk, rv in v.items() if rk != \"multiplier\"} for k, v in models.items()},\n            \"ttft_corrections\": {k: float(v) for k, v in ttft_corrections.items()},\n            \"itl_data\": itl_data,\n        }\n        with open(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"h1_summary.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n            json.dump(summary, f, indent=2, default=str)\n    else:\n        print(\"\\nERROR: No experiments completed successfully!\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e652145f-d03b-4eb5-bbf8-d7db257fe10a","uuid":"cbd36984-38ed-4ba6-8b6c-c7358d1513fe"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RGmKvSngN3mGp81QfrkEPf","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/stepml-worktrees/round4-idea-3-hybrid-calibration/hypotheses/h-stepml/round4/idea-3-hybrid-calibration/h1-principled-base/run.py has been updated. Here's the result of running `cat -n` on a snippet of the edited file:\n     1→#!/usr/bin/env python3\n     2→\"\"\"H1: Stage 1 Principled Base — Overhead-Scaled Step Time + TTFT Corrections.\n     3→\n     4→Key insight from R3: BLIS simulates a \"faster universe\" (~40% of real time).\n     5→The root cause is that step.duration_us measures only GPU forward-pass time,\n     6→while real step cycle time includes CPU scheduling overhead, CUDA sync, and\n     7→memory management. The overhead floor (max(overhead, compute)) is the right\n     8→mechanism but needs calibration from lifecycle data.\n     9→\n    10→This script:\n    11→1. Computes per-model median ITL from lifecycle data (the true step cycle time)\n    12→2. Computes per-model median step.duration_us (GPU-only time)\n    13→3. Derives overhead_multiplier = median_ITL / median_duration (typically ~2-3x)\n    14→4. Trains per-model regime regression on SCALED step times (duration * multiplier)\n    15→5. Applies TTFT additive corrections from lifecycle data\n    16→6. Exports StepML artifacts and runs BLIS validation\n    17→\"\"\"\n    18→\n    19→import json\n    20→import os\n    21→import sys\n    22→\n    23→import numpy as np\n    24→import pandas as pd\n    25→from sklearn.linear_model import Ridge\n    26→\n    27→# Add shared infrastructure to path\n    28→_SCRIPT_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))\n    29→_IDEA_DIR = os.path.dirname(_SCRIPT_DIR)\n    30→_SHARED_DIR = os.path.join(_IDEA_DIR, \"..\", \"..\", \"shared\")\n    31→sys.path.insert(0, _SHARED_DIR)\n    32→\n    33→from data_loader import (\n    34→    load_all_experiments,\n    35→    load_lifecycle_data,\n    36→    parse_experiment_metadata,\n    37→    DEFAULT_DATA_ROOT,\n    38→)\n    39→from evaluation import compute_mape\n    40→from validate_blis import DEFAULT_BINARY\n    41→\n    42→OUTPUT_DIR = os.path.join(_SCRIPT_DIR, \"output\")\n    43→os.makedirs(OUTPUT_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n    44→\n    45→\n    46→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    47→# Step 1: Compute per-model ITL from lifecycle data\n    48→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    49→def compute_per_model_itl(data_root: str) -> dict:\n    50→    \"\"\"Compute per-model median inter-token latency from lifecycle data.\n    51→\n    52→    ITL = median of (output_token_times[i+1] - output_token_times[i]) for all\n    53→    requests in all experiments for each model. This is the true step cycle time\n    54→    as seen by the client (GPU compute + CPU overhead + CUDA sync).\n    55→    \"\"\"\n    56→    model_itls = {}  # {model: [itl_values]}\n    57→\n    58→    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(data_root)):\n    59→        dirpath = os.path.join(data_root, dirname)\n    60→        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n    61→            continue\n    62→        lifecycle_path = os.path.join(\n    63→            dirpath, \"results\", \"per_request_lifecycle_metrics.json\"\n    64→        )\n    65→        if not os.path.isfile(lifecycle_path):\n    66→            continue\n    67→\n    68→        meta = parse_experiment_metadata(dirname)\n    69→        model = meta[\"model\"]\n    70→\n    71→        try:\n    72→            lifecycle_df = load_lifecycle_data(dirpath)\n    73→        except Exception:\n    74→            continue\n    75→\n    76→        itls = []\n    77→        for _, row in lifecycle_df.iterrows():\n    78→            times = row.get(\"output_token_times\", [])\n    79→            if not times or len(times) < 2:\n    80→                continue\n    81→            for i in range(1, len(times)):\n    82→                iti_s = times[i] - times[i - 1]\n    83→                if iti_s > 0:\n    84→                    itls.append(iti_s * 1_000_000)  # convert to us\n    85→\n    86→        if itls:\n    87→            model_itls.setdefault(model, []).extend(itls)\n    88→\n    89→    result = {}\n    90→    for model, itls in model_itls.items():\n    91→        arr = np.array(itls)\n    92→        result[model] = {\n    93→            \"median_itl_us\": float(np.median(arr)),\n    94→            \"mean_itl_us\": float(np.mean(arr)),\n    95→            \"p10_itl_us\": float(np.percentile(arr, 10)),\n    96→            \"p90_itl_us\": float(np.percentile(arr, 90)),\n    97→            \"n_tokens\": len(arr),\n    98→        }\n    99→        print(\n   100→            f\"  {model}: median_ITL={result[model]['median_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"\n   101→            f\"mean_ITL={result[model]['mean_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"\n   102→            f\"p10={result[model]['p10_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"\n   103→            f\"p90={result[model]['p90_itl_us']:.0f}us, n={len(arr)}\"\n   104→        )\n   105→\n   106→    return result\n   107→\n   108→\n   109→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   110→# Step 2: Compute overhead multiplier per model\n   111→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   112→def compute_overhead_multipliers(\n   113→    step_df: pd.DataFrame, itl_data: dict\n   114→) -> dict:\n   115→    \"\"\"Compute per-model overhead multiplier = median_ITL / median_step_duration.\n   116→\n   117→    This captures the ratio of real cycle time (ITL) to GPU-only time (duration).\n   118→    \"\"\"\n   119→    multipliers = {}\n   120→    for model in sorted(step_df[\"model\"].unique()):\n   121→        mdf = step_df[step_df[\"model\"] == model]\n   122→        dur = mdf[\"step.duration_us\"].dropna()\n   123→        if len(dur) == 0:\n   124→            continue\n   125→\n   126→        median_dur = float(dur.median())\n   127→        itl_info = itl_data.get(model)\n   128→        if itl_info is None:\n   129→            # Try normalized name\n   130→            for k, v in itl_data.items():\n   131→                if k.replace(\"-hf\", \"\") == model.replace(\"-hf\", \"\"):\n   132→                    itl_info = v\n   133→                    break\n   134→\n   135→        if itl_info is None:\n   136→            print(f\"  {model}: no ITL data, using 2.0x default multiplier\")\n   137→            multipliers[model] = {\n   138→                \"multiplier\": 2.0,\n   139→                \"median_dur_us\": median_dur,\n   140→                \"median_itl_us\": median_dur * 2.0,\n   141→            }\n   142→            continue\n   143→\n   144→        median_itl = itl_info[\"median_itl_us\"]\n   145→        mult = median_itl / median_dur if median_dur > 0 else 2.0\n   146→\n   147→        # Clamp to reasonable range [1.2, 10.0]\n   148→        mult = max(1.2, min(10.0, mult))\n   149→\n   150→        multipliers[model] = {\n   151→            \"multiplier\": float(mult),\n   152→            \"median_dur_us\": float(median_dur),\n   153→            \"median_itl_us\": float(median_itl),\n   154→        }\n   155→        print(\n   156→            f\"  {model}: multiplier={mult:.2f}x \"\n   157→            f\"(median_ITL={median_itl:.0f}us / median_dur={median_dur:.0f}us)\"\n   158→        )\n   159→\n   160→    return multipliers\n   161→\n   162→\n   163→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   164→# Step 3: Train per-model regression on overhead-scaled step times\n   165→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   166→def train_per_model_regression(\n   167→    step_df: pd.DataFrame, multipliers: dict\n   168→) -> dict:\n   169→    \"\"\"Train per-model regime regression on overhead-scaled step times.\n   170→\n   171→    target = step.duration_us * overhead_multiplier (the estimated cycle time)\n   172→    features = [scheduled_tokens, num_decode_reqs]\n   173→    \"\"\"\n   174→    models = {}\n   175→\n   176→    for model_name in sorted(step_df[\"model\"].unique()):\n   177→        mdf = step_df[step_df[\"model\"] == model_name].copy()\n   178→        mult_info = multipliers.get(model_name, {\"multiplier\": 2.0})\n   179→        mult = mult_info[\"multiplier\"]\n   180→\n   181→        # Compute scaled target\n   182→        mdf = mdf.dropna(subset=[\"step.duration_us\"])\n   183→        mdf[\"scaled_duration_us\"] = mdf[\"step.duration_us\"].astype(float) * mult\n   184→\n   185→        # Feature columns\n   186→        if \"batch.scheduled_tokens\" in mdf.columns:\n   187→            mdf[\"new_tokens\"] = mdf[\"batch.scheduled_tokens\"].astype(float)\n   188→        else:\n   189→            mdf[\"new_tokens\"] = (\n   190→                mdf.get(\"batch.prefill_tokens\", pd.Series(0, index=mdf.index)).astype(float)\n   191→                + mdf.get(\"batch.decode_tokens\", pd.Series(0, index=mdf.index)).astype(float)\n   192→            )\n   193→\n   194→        mdf[\"n_decode_reqs\"] = mdf.get(\n   195→            \"batch.num_decode_reqs\", pd.Series(0, index=mdf.index)\n   196→        ).astype(float)\n   197→\n   198→        # Regime separation\n   199→        if \"batch.prefill_tokens\" in mdf.columns:\n   200→            decode_only = mdf[mdf[\"batch.prefill_tokens\"] == 0]\n   201→            mixed = mdf[mdf[\"batch.prefill_tokens\"] > 0]\n   202→        else:\n   203→            decode_only = mdf\n   204→            mixed = mdf.iloc[0:0]\n   205→\n   206→        regimes = {\"multiplier\": mult}\n   207→\n   208→        # Train decode-only\n   209→        if len(decode_only) >= 10:\n   210→            X = decode_only[[\"new_tokens\", \"n_decode_reqs\"]].values\n   211→            y = decode_only[\"scaled_duration_us\"].values\n   212→            reg = Ridge(alpha=10.0)\n   213→            reg.fit(X, y)\n   214→            pred = reg.predict(X)\n   215→            mape = compute_mape(pred, y)\n   216→            regimes[\"decode_only\"] = {\n   217→                \"intercept\": float(reg.intercept_),\n   218→                \"coeff_new_tokens\": float(reg.coef_[0]),\n   219→                \"coeff_n_decode_reqs\": float(reg.coef_[1]),\n   220→                \"mape\": mape,\n   221→                \"n\": len(decode_only),\n   222→                \"mean_target\": float(y.mean()),\n   223→            }\n   224→            print(\n   225→                f\"  {model_name} decode-only: intercept={reg.intercept_:.0f}, \"\n   226→                f\"b_tokens={reg.coef_[0]:.2f}, b_reqs={reg.coef_[1]:.2f}, \"\n   227→                f\"MAPE={mape:.1f}%, n={len(decode_only)}\"\n   228→            )\n   229→\n   230→        # Train mixed\n   231→        if len(mixed) >= 10:\n   232→            X = mixed[[\"new_tokens\", \"n_decode_reqs\"]].values\n   233→            y = mixed[\"scaled_duration_us\"].values\n   234→            reg = Ridge(alpha=10.0)\n   235→            reg.fit(X, y)\n   236→            pred = reg.predict(X)\n   237→            mape = compute_mape(pred, y)\n   238→            regimes[\"mixed\"] = {\n   239→                \"intercept\": float(reg.intercept_),\n   240→                \"coeff_new_tokens\": float(reg.coef_[0]),\n   241→                \"coeff_n_decode_reqs\": float(reg.coef_[1]),\n   242→                \"mape\": mape,\n   243→                \"n\": len(mixed),\n   244→                \"mean_target\": float(y.mean()),\n   245→            }\n   246→            print(\n   247→                f\"  {model_name} mixed:       intercept={reg.intercept_:.0f}, \"\n   248→                f\"b_tokens={reg.coef_[0]:.2f}, b_reqs={reg.coef_[1]:.2f}, \"\n   249→                f\"MAPE={mape:.1f}%, n={len(mixed)}\"\n   250→            )\n   251→\n   252→        # Global\n   253→        X = mdf[[\"new_tokens\", \"n_decode_reqs\"]].values\n   254→        y = mdf[\"scaled_duration_us\"].values\n   255→        reg = Ridge(alpha=10.0)\n   256→        reg.fit(X, y)\n   257→        pred = reg.predict(X)\n   258→        mape = compute_mape(pred, y)\n   259→        regimes[\"global\"] = {\n   260→            \"intercept\": float(reg.intercept_),\n   261→            \"coeff_new_tokens\": float(reg.coef_[0]),\n   262→            \"coeff_n_decode_reqs\": float(reg.coef_[1]),\n   263→            \"mape\": mape,\n   264→            \"n\": len(mdf),\n   265→            \"mean_target\": float(y.mean()),\n   266→        }\n   267→\n   268→        models[model_name] = regimes\n   269→\n   270→    return models\n   271→\n   272→\n   273→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   274→# Step 4: TTFT corrections from lifecycle data\n   275→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   276→def estimate_ttft_corrections(data_root: str) -> dict:\n   277→    \"\"\"Per-model TTFT correction = observed mean TTFT from lifecycle data.\"\"\"\n   278→    corrections = {}\n   279→    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(data_root)):\n   280→        dirpath = os.path.join(data_root, dirname)\n   281→        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n   282→            continue\n   283→        lifecycle_path = os.path.join(\n   284→            dirpath, \"results\", \"per_request_lifecycle_metrics.json\"\n   285→        )\n   286→        if not os.path.isfile(lifecycle_path):\n   287→            continue\n   288→\n   289→        meta = parse_experiment_metadata(dirname)\n   290→        model = meta[\"model\"]\n   291→\n   292→        try:\n   293→            lifecycle_df = load_lifecycle_data(dirpath)\n   294→        except Exception:\n   295→            continue\n   296→\n   297→        ttft_values = []\n   298→        for _, row in lifecycle_df.iterrows():\n   299→            times = row.get(\"output_token_times\", [])\n   300→            start = row.get(\"start_time\", 0)\n   301→            if times and len(times) > 0 and start > 0:\n   302→                ttft_s = times[0] - start\n   303→                if ttft_s > 0:\n   304→                    ttft_values.append(ttft_s)\n   305→\n   306→        if ttft_values:\n   307→            corrections.setdefault(model, []).extend(ttft_values)\n   308→\n   309→    result = {}\n   310→    for model, values in corrections.items():\n   311→        mean_ttft_us = float(np.mean(values)) * 1_000_000\n   312→        result[model] = mean_ttft_us\n   313→        print(f\"  TTFT correction for {model}: {mean_ttft_us:.0f}us ({mean_ttft_us/1000:.1f}ms)\")\n   314→\n   315→    return result\n   316→\n   317→\n   318→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   319→# Step 5: Export StepML artifacts\n   320→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   321→def export_stepml_artifact(\n   322→    model_name: str, regimes: dict, ttft_correction_us: float, output_path: str\n   323→) -> dict:\n   324→    \"\"\"Export per-model StepML JSON artifact.\"\"\"\n   325→    mult = regimes.get(\"multiplier\", 2.0)\n   326→\n   327→    # Use decode-only intercept as overhead floor\n   328→    if \"decode_only\" in regimes:\n   329→        d = regimes[\"decode_only\"]\n   330→        overhead_us = max(d[\"intercept\"], 1000)\n   331→    elif \"global\" in regimes:\n   332→        overhead_us = max(regimes[\"global\"][\"intercept\"], 1000)\n   333→    else:\n   334→        overhead_us = 4000\n   335→\n   336→    step_time_regimes = []\n   337→\n   338→    if \"decode_only\" in regimes:\n   339→        d = regimes[\"decode_only\"]\n   340→        step_time_regimes.append(\n   341→            {\n   342→                \"name\": \"decode_only\",\n   343→                \"condition\": {\"feature\": \"prefill_tokens\", \"op\": \"==\", \"value\": 0},\n   344→                \"model\": {\n   345→                    \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n   346→                    \"intercept\": d[\"intercept\"],\n   347→                    \"feature_coefficients\": {\n   348→                        \"decode_tokens\": d[\"coeff_new_tokens\"],\n   349→                        \"num_decode_reqs\": d[\"coeff_n_decode_reqs\"],\n   350→                    },\n   351→                },\n   352→            }\n   353→        )\n   354→\n   355→    if \"mixed\" in regimes:\n   356→        m = regimes[\"mixed\"]\n   357→        step_time_regimes.append(\n   358→            {\n   359→                \"name\": \"mixed\",\n   360→                \"condition\": None,\n   361→                \"model\": {\n   362→                    \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n   363→                    \"intercept\": m[\"intercept\"],\n   364→                    \"feature_coefficients\": {\n   365→                        \"scheduled_tokens\": m[\"coeff_new_tokens\"],\n   366→                        \"num_decode_reqs\": m[\"coeff_n_decode_reqs\"],\n   367→                    },\n   368→                },\n   369→            }\n   370→        )\n   371→\n   372→    if not step_time_regimes:\n   373→        g = regimes[\"global\"]\n   374→        step_time_regimes.append(\n   375→            {\n   376→                \"name\": \"global\",\n   377→                \"condition\": None,\n   378→                \"model\": {\n   379→                    \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n   380→                    \"intercept\": g[\"intercept\"],\n   381→                    \"feature_coefficients\": {\n   382→                        \"scheduled_tokens\": g[\"coeff_new_tokens\"],\n   383→                        \"num_decode_reqs\": g[\"coeff_n_decode_reqs\"],\n   384→                    },\n   385→                },\n   386→            }\n   387→        )\n   388→\n   389→    artifact = {\n   390→        \"version\": 2,\n   391→        \"step_time_regimes\": step_time_regimes,\n   392→        \"step_overhead_us\": overhead_us,\n   393→        \"output_token_processing_time_us\": 0,\n   394→        \"scheduling_processing_time_us\": 0,\n   395→        \"preemption_processing_time_us\": 0,\n   396→    }\n   397→\n   398→    if ttft_correction_us > 0:\n   399→        artifact[\"queueing_time\"] = {\n   400→            \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n   401→            \"intercept\": ttft_correction_us,\n   402→            \"feature_coefficients\": {},\n   403→        }\n   404→\n   405→    with open(output_path, \"w\") as f:\n   406→        json.dump(artifact, f, indent=2)\n   407→\n   408→    print(\n   409→        f\"  {model_name}: overhead={overhead_us:.0f}us, \"\n   410→        f\"TTFT={ttft_correction_us:.0f}us, mult={mult:.2f}x\"\n   411→    )\n   412→    return artifact\n   413→\n   414→\n   415→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   416→# Step 6: BLIS validation\n   417→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   418→def run_blis_validation_per_model(\n   419→    data_root: str, artifacts: dict, output_csv: str\n   420→) -> pd.DataFrame:\n   421→    \"\"\"Run BLIS validation with per-model StepML artifacts.\"\"\"\n   422→    from validate_blis import (\n   423→        parse_experiment_dir,\n   424→        load_ground_truth_metrics,\n   425→        load_exp_config,\n   426→        extract_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log,\n   427→        extract_cpu_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log,\n   428→        load_profile,\n   429→        build_workload_spec,\n   430→        run_blis,\n   431→        compute_error,\n   432→    )\n   433→    import tempfile\n   434→    import yaml\n   435→\n   436→    binary = DEFAULT_BINARY\n   437→    if not os.path.isfile(binary):\n   438→        import subprocess\n   439→        repo_root = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(_SHARED_DIR, \"..\", \"..\", \"..\"))\n   440→        subprocess.run([\"go\", \"build\", \"-o\", binary, \"main.go\"], cwd=repo_root, check=True)\n   441→\n   442→    results = []\n   443→    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(data_root)):\n   444→        dirpath = os.path.join(data_root, dirname)\n   445→        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n   446→            continue\n   447→        summary_path = os.path.join(dirpath, \"results\", \"summary_lifecycle_metrics.json\")\n   448→        if not os.path.isfile(summary_path):\n   449→            continue\n   450→\n   451→        try:\n   452→            meta = parse_experiment_dir(dirname)\n   453→        except ValueError:\n   454→            continue\n   455→\n   456→        model_name = meta[\"model\"]\n   457→\n   458→        # Find matching artifact\n   459→        artifact_path = None\n   460→        for art_model, art_path in artifacts.items():\n   461→            if art_model == model_name:\n   462→                artifact_path = art_path\n   463→                break\n   464→        if artifact_path is None:\n   465→            for art_model, art_path in artifacts.items():\n   466→                if art_model.replace(\"-hf\", \"\") == model_name.replace(\"-hf\", \"\"):\n   467→                    artifact_path = art_path\n   468→                    break\n   469→        if artifact_path is None:\n   470→            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"no_artifact\"})\n   471→            continue\n   472→\n   473→        gt = load_ground_truth_metrics(dirpath)\n   474→        exp_config = load_exp_config(dirpath)\n   475→        total_kv_blocks = extract_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log(dirpath)\n   476→        cpu_kv_blocks = extract_cpu_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log(dirpath)\n   477→\n   478→        if total_kv_blocks is None:\n   479→            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"no_kv_blocks\"})\n   480→            continue\n   481→\n   482→        try:\n   483→            profile = load_profile(dirpath)\n   484→        except Exception:\n   485→            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"no_profile\"})\n   486→            continue\n   487→\n   488→        workload_spec = build_workload_spec(profile, gt)\n   489→\n   490→        with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(mode=\"w\", suffix=\".yaml\", delete=False) as f:\n   491→            yaml.dump(workload_spec, f, default_flow_style=False)\n   492→            spec_path = f.name\n   493→\n   494→        with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(suffix=\".json\", delete=False) as f:\n   495→            results_json_path = f.name\n   496→\n   497→        try:\n   498→            blis_metrics = run_blis(\n   499→                binary=binary,\n   500→                workload_spec_path=spec_path,\n   501→                exp_config=exp_config,\n   502→                total_kv_blocks=total_kv_blocks,\n   503→                alpha_coeffs=[0, 0, 0],\n   504→                beta_coeffs=[0, 0, 0],\n   505→                results_path=results_json_path,\n   506→                stepml_model_path=artifact_path,\n   507→                cpu_kv_blocks=cpu_kv_blocks,\n   508→            )\n   509→        finally:\n   510→            os.unlink(spec_path)\n   511→            if os.path.exists(results_json_path):\n   512→                os.unlink(results_json_path)\n   513→\n   514→        if blis_metrics is None:\n   515→            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"blis_failed\"})\n   516→            continue\n   517→\n   518→        e2e_err = compute_error(blis_metrics[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], gt[\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   519→        ttft_err = compute_error(blis_metrics[\"ttft_mean_ms\"], gt[\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   520→        itl_err = compute_error(blis_metrics[\"itl_mean_ms\"], gt[\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   521→\n   522→        print(f\"  {dirname}: E2E={e2e_err*100:.1f}%, TTFT={ttft_err*100:.1f}%, ITL={itl_err*100:.1f}%\")\n   523→\n   524→        results.append({\n   525→            \"experiment\": dirname,\n   526→            \"model\": model_name,\n   527→            \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"],\n   528→            \"tp\": meta[\"tp\"],\n   529→            \"status\": \"ok\",\n   530→            \"gt_e2e_ms\": gt[\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   531→            \"gt_ttft_ms\": gt[\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   532→            \"gt_itl_ms\": gt[\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   533→            \"blis_e2e_ms\": blis_metrics[\"e2e_mean_ms\"],\n   534→            \"blis_ttft_ms\": blis_metrics[\"ttft_mean_ms\"],\n   535→            \"blis_itl_ms\": blis_metrics[\"itl_mean_ms\"],\n   536→            \"e2e_error\": e2e_err,\n   537→            \"ttft_error\": ttft_err,\n   538→            \"itl_error\": itl_err,\n   539→            \"blis_completed\": blis_metrics[\"completed_requests\"],\n   540→            \"gt_requests\": gt[\"num_requests\"],\n   541→        })\n   542→\n   543→    df = pd.DataFrame(results)\n   544→    df.to_csv(output_csv, index=False)\n   545→    return df\n   546→\n   547→\n   548→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   549→# Main\n   550→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   551→def main():\n   552→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n   553→    print(\"H1: Stage 1 Principled Base — Overhead-Scaled + TTFT Corrections\")\n   554→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n   555→\n   556→    data_root = DEFAULT_DATA_ROOT\n   557→\n   558→    # Step 1: Compute ITL from lifecycle data\n   559→    print(\"\\n--- Step 1: Per-model ITL from lifecycle data ---\")\n   560→    itl_data = compute_per_model_itl(data_root)\n   561→\n   562→    # Step 2: Load step data and compute multipliers\n   563→    print(\"\\n--- Step 2: Compute overhead multipliers ---\")\n   564→    step_df = load_all_experiments(data_root)\n   565→    multipliers = compute_overhead_multipliers(step_df, itl_data)\n   566→\n   567→    # Step 3: Train regression on scaled step times\n   568→    print(\"\\n--- Step 3: Train per-model regression on scaled step times ---\")\n   569→    models = train_per_model_regression(step_df, multipliers)\n   570→\n   571→    with open(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"regression_results.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n   572→        json.dump(models, f, indent=2, default=str)\n   573→\n   574→    # Step 4: TTFT corrections\n   575→    print(\"\\n--- Step 4: TTFT corrections ---\")\n   576→    ttft_corrections = estimate_ttft_corrections(data_root)\n   577→\n   578→    # Step 5: Export artifacts\n   579→    print(\"\\n--- Step 5: Export StepML artifacts ---\")\n   580→    artifact_dir = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"artifacts\")\n   581→    os.makedirs(artifact_dir, exist_ok=True)\n   582→\n   583→    artifacts = {}\n   584→    for model_name, regimes in models.items():\n   585→        ttft_us = 0\n   586→        for ttft_model, ttft_val in ttft_corrections.items():\n   587→            if ttft_model == model_name or ttft_model.replace(\"-hf\", \"\") == model_name.replace(\"-hf\", \"\"):\n   588→                ttft_us = ttft_val\n   589→                break\n   590→\n   591→        artifact_path = os.path.join(artifact_dir, f\"{model_name}.json\")\n   592→        export_stepml_artifact(model_name, regimes, ttft_us, artifact_path)\n   593→        artifacts[model_name] = artifact_path\n   594→\n   595→    # Step 6: BLIS validation\n   596→    print(\"\\n--- Step 6: BLIS validation ---\")\n   597→    results_csv = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"blis_validation.csv\")\n   598→    results_df = run_blis_validation_per_model(data_root, artifacts, results_csv)\n   599→\n   600→    # Summary\n   601→    ok = results_df[results_df[\"status\"] == \"ok\"]\n   602→    if len(ok) > 0:\n   603→        mean_e2e = ok[\"e2e_error\"].mean() * 100\n   604→        mean_ttft = ok[\"ttft_error\"].mean() * 100\n   605→        mean_itl = ok[\"itl_error\"].mean() * 100\n   606→\n   607→        print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\n   608→        print(\"STAGE 1 RESULTS SUMMARY\")\n   609→        print(\"=\" * 70)\n   610→        print(f\"Experiments: {len(ok)}\")\n   611→        print(f\"Mean E2E:  {mean_e2e:.1f}% (target <30%)\")\n   612→        print(f\"Mean TTFT: {mean_ttft:.1f}%\")\n   613→        print(f\"Mean ITL:  {mean_itl:.1f}% (target <20%)\")\n   614→        below_10 = (ok[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.10).sum()\n   615→        print(f\"E2E < 10%: {below_10}/{len(ok)}\")\n   616→\n   617→        print(f\"\\n{'Experiment':<55} {'E2E%':>7} {'TTFT%':>7} {'ITL%':>7}\")\n   618→        print(\"-\" * 80)\n   619→        for _, row in ok.iterrows():\n   620→            print(\n   621→                f\"{row['experiment']:<55} {row['e2e_error']*100:>7.1f} \"\n   622→                f\"{row['ttft_error']*100:>7.1f} {row['itl_error']*100:>7.1f}\"\n   623→            )\n   624→        print(\"-\" * 80)\n   625→        print(f\"{'MEAN':<55} {mean_e2e:>7.1f} {mean_ttft:>7.1f} {mean_itl:>7.1f}\")\n   626→\n   627→        # Save summary\n   628→        summary = {\n   629→            \"mean_e2e_error\": mean_e2e,\n   630→            \"mean_ttft_error\": mean_ttft,\n   631→            \"mean_itl_error\": mean_itl,\n   632→            \"n_experiments\": len(ok),\n   633→            \"n_below_10_e2e\": int(below_10),\n   634→            \"per_experiment\": ok[\n   635→                [\"experiment\", \"model\", \"workload\", \"e2e_error\", \"ttft_error\", \"itl_error\",\n   636→                 \"gt_e2e_ms\", \"blis_e2e_ms\", \"gt_itl_ms\", \"blis_itl_ms\"]\n   637→            ].to_dict(\"records\"),\n   638→            \"multipliers\": multipliers,\n   639→            \"regression_results\": {k: {rk: rv for rk, rv in v.items() if rk != \"multiplier\"} for k, v in models.items()},\n   640→            \"ttft_corrections\": {k: float(v) for k, v in ttft_corrections.items()},\n   641→            \"itl_data\": itl_data,\n   642→        }\n   643→        with open(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"h1_summary.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n   644→            json.dump(summary, f, indent=2, default=str)\n   645→    else:\n   646→        print(\"\\nERROR: No experiments completed successfully!\")\n   647→        sys.exit(1)\n   648→\n   649→\n   650→if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n   651→    main()\n   652→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e652145f-d03b-4eb5-bbf8-d7db257fe10a","uuid":"6d7dc5bd-1f0b-456a-87bb-40a5934bc878","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/stepml-worktrees/round4-idea-3-hybrid-calibration/hypotheses/h-stepml/round4/idea-3-hybrid-calibration/h1-principled-base/run.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"H1: Stage 1 Principled Base — Overhead-Scaled Step Time + TTFT Corrections.\n\nKey insight from R3: BLIS simulates a \"faster universe\" (~40% of real time).\nThe root cause is that step.duration_us measures only GPU forward-pass time,\nwhile real step cycle time includes CPU scheduling overhead, CUDA sync, and\nmemory management. The overhead floor (max(overhead, compute)) is the right\nmechanism but needs calibration from lifecycle data.\n\nThis script:\n1. Computes per-model median ITL from lifecycle data (the true step cycle time)\n2. Computes per-model median step.duration_us (GPU-only time)\n3. Derives overhead_multiplier = median_ITL / median_duration (typically ~2-3x)\n4. Trains per-model regime regression on SCALED step times (duration * multiplier)\n5. Applies TTFT additive corrections from lifecycle data\n6. Exports StepML artifacts and runs BLIS validation\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport os\nimport sys\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import Ridge\n\n# Add shared infrastructure to path\n_SCRIPT_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))\n_IDEA_DIR = os.path.dirname(_SCRIPT_DIR)\n_SHARED_DIR = os.path.join(_IDEA_DIR, \"..\", \"..\", \"shared\")\nsys.path.insert(0, _SHARED_DIR)\n\nfrom data_loader import (\n    load_all_experiments,\n    load_lifecycle_data,\n    parse_experiment_metadata,\n    DEFAULT_DATA_ROOT,\n)\nfrom evaluation import compute_mape\nfrom validate_blis import DEFAULT_BINARY\n\nOUTPUT_DIR = os.path.join(_SCRIPT_DIR, \"output\")\nos.makedirs(OUTPUT_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 1: Compute per-model ITL from lifecycle data\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef compute_per_model_itl(data_root: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Compute per-model median inter-token latency from lifecycle data.\n\n    ITL = median of (output_token_times[i+1] - output_token_times[i]) for all\n    requests in all experiments for each model. This is the true step cycle time\n    as seen by the client (GPU compute + CPU overhead + CUDA sync).\n    \"\"\"\n    model_itls = {}  # {model: [itl_values]}\n\n    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(data_root)):\n        dirpath = os.path.join(data_root, dirname)\n        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n            continue\n        lifecycle_path = os.path.join(\n            dirpath, \"results\", \"per_request_lifecycle_metrics.json\"\n        )\n        if not os.path.isfile(lifecycle_path):\n            continue\n\n        meta = parse_experiment_metadata(dirname)\n        model = meta[\"model\"]\n\n        try:\n            lifecycle_df = load_lifecycle_data(dirpath)\n        except Exception:\n            continue\n\n        itls = []\n        for _, row in lifecycle_df.iterrows():\n            times = row.get(\"output_token_times\", [])\n            if not times or len(times) < 2:\n                continue\n            for i in range(1, len(times)):\n                iti_s = times[i] - times[i - 1]\n                if iti_s > 0:\n                    itls.append(iti_s * 1_000_000)  # convert to us\n\n        if itls:\n            model_itls.setdefault(model, []).extend(itls)\n\n    result = {}\n    for model, itls in model_itls.items():\n        arr = np.array(itls)\n        result[model] = {\n            \"median_itl_us\": float(np.median(arr)),\n            \"mean_itl_us\": float(np.mean(arr)),\n            \"p10_itl_us\": float(np.percentile(arr, 10)),\n            \"p90_itl_us\": float(np.percentile(arr, 90)),\n            \"n_tokens\": len(arr),\n        }\n        print(\n            f\"  {model}: median_ITL={result[model]['median_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"\n            f\"mean_ITL={result[model]['mean_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"\n            f\"p10={result[model]['p10_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"\n            f\"p90={result[model]['p90_itl_us']:.0f}us, n={len(arr)}\"\n        )\n\n    return result\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 2: Compute overhead multiplier per model\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef compute_overhead_multipliers(\n    step_df: pd.DataFrame, itl_data: dict\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Compute per-model overhead multiplier = median_ITL / median_step_duration.\n\n    This captures the ratio of real cycle time (ITL) to GPU-only time (duration).\n    \"\"\"\n    multipliers = {}\n    for model in sorted(step_df[\"model\"].unique()):\n        mdf = step_df[step_df[\"model\"] == model]\n        dur = mdf[\"step.duration_us\"].dropna()\n        if len(dur) == 0:\n            continue\n\n        median_dur = float(dur.median())\n        itl_info = itl_data.get(model)\n        if itl_info is None:\n            # Try normalized name\n            for k, v in itl_data.items():\n                if k.replace(\"-hf\", \"\") == model.replace(\"-hf\", \"\"):\n                    itl_info = v\n                    break\n\n        if itl_info is None:\n            print(f\"  {model}: no ITL data, using 2.0x default multiplier\")\n            multipliers[model] = {\n                \"multiplier\": 2.0,\n                \"median_dur_us\": median_dur,\n                \"median_itl_us\": median_dur * 2.0,\n            }\n            continue\n\n        median_itl = itl_info[\"median_itl_us\"]\n        mult = median_itl / median_dur if median_dur > 0 else 2.0\n\n        # Clamp to reasonable range [1.2, 10.0]\n        mult = max(1.2, min(10.0, mult))\n\n        multipliers[model] = {\n            \"multiplier\": float(mult),\n            \"median_dur_us\": float(median_dur),\n            \"median_itl_us\": float(median_itl),\n        }\n        print(\n            f\"  {model}: multiplier={mult:.2f}x \"\n            f\"(median_ITL={median_itl:.0f}us / median_dur={median_dur:.0f}us)\"\n        )\n\n    return multipliers\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 3: Train per-model regression on overhead-scaled step times\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef train_per_model_regression(\n    step_df: pd.DataFrame, multipliers: dict\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Train per-model regime regression on overhead-scaled step times.\n\n    target = step.duration_us * overhead_multiplier (the estimated cycle time)\n    features = [scheduled_tokens, num_decode_reqs]\n    \"\"\"\n    models = {}\n\n    for model_name in sorted(step_df[\"model\"].unique()):\n        mdf = step_df[step_df[\"model\"] == model_name].copy()\n        mult_info = multipliers.get(model_name, {\"multiplier\": 2.0})\n        mult = mult_info[\"multiplier\"]\n\n        # Compute scaled target\n        mdf = mdf.dropna(subset=[\"step.duration_us\"])\n        mdf[\"scaled_duration_us\"] = mdf[\"step.duration_us\"].astype(float) * mult\n\n        # Feature columns\n        if \"batch.scheduled_tokens\" in mdf.columns:\n            mdf[\"new_tokens\"] = mdf[\"batch.scheduled_tokens\"].astype(float)\n        else:\n            mdf[\"new_tokens\"] = (\n                mdf.get(\"batch.prefill_tokens\", pd.Series(0, index=mdf.index)).astype(float)\n                + mdf.get(\"batch.decode_tokens\", pd.Series(0, index=mdf.index)).astype(float)\n            )\n\n        mdf[\"n_decode_reqs\"] = mdf.get(\n            \"batch.num_decode_reqs\", pd.Series(0, index=mdf.index)\n        ).astype(float)\n\n        # Regime separation\n        if \"batch.prefill_tokens\" in mdf.columns:\n            decode_only = mdf[mdf[\"batch.prefill_tokens\"] == 0]\n            mixed = mdf[mdf[\"batch.prefill_tokens\"] > 0]\n        else:\n            decode_only = mdf\n            mixed = mdf.iloc[0:0]\n\n        regimes = {\"multiplier\": mult}\n\n        # Train decode-only\n        if len(decode_only) >= 10:\n            X = decode_only[[\"new_tokens\", \"n_decode_reqs\"]].values\n            y = decode_only[\"scaled_duration_us\"].values\n            reg = Ridge(alpha=10.0)\n            reg.fit(X, y)\n            pred = reg.predict(X)\n            mape = compute_mape(pred, y)\n            regimes[\"decode_only\"] = {\n                \"intercept\": float(reg.intercept_),\n                \"coeff_new_tokens\": float(reg.coef_[0]),\n                \"coeff_n_decode_reqs\": float(reg.coef_[1]),\n                \"mape\": mape,\n                \"n\": len(decode_only),\n                \"mean_target\": float(y.mean()),\n            }\n            print(\n                f\"  {model_name} decode-only: intercept={reg.intercept_:.0f}, \"\n                f\"b_tokens={reg.coef_[0]:.2f}, b_reqs={reg.coef_[1]:.2f}, \"\n                f\"MAPE={mape:.1f}%, n={len(decode_only)}\"\n            )\n\n        # Train mixed\n        if len(mixed) >= 10:\n            X = mixed[[\"new_tokens\", \"n_decode_reqs\"]].values\n            y = mixed[\"scaled_duration_us\"].values\n            reg = Ridge(alpha=10.0)\n            reg.fit(X, y)\n            pred = reg.predict(X)\n            mape = compute_mape(pred, y)\n            regimes[\"mixed\"] = {\n                \"intercept\": float(reg.intercept_),\n                \"coeff_new_tokens\": float(reg.coef_[0]),\n                \"coeff_n_decode_reqs\": float(reg.coef_[1]),\n                \"mape\": mape,\n                \"n\": len(mixed),\n                \"mean_target\": float(y.mean()),\n            }\n            print(\n                f\"  {model_name} mixed:       intercept={reg.intercept_:.0f}, \"\n                f\"b_tokens={reg.coef_[0]:.2f}, b_reqs={reg.coef_[1]:.2f}, \"\n                f\"MAPE={mape:.1f}%, n={len(mixed)}\"\n            )\n\n        # Global\n        X = mdf[[\"new_tokens\", \"n_decode_reqs\"]].values\n        y = mdf[\"scaled_duration_us\"].values\n        reg = Ridge(alpha=10.0)\n        reg.fit(X, y)\n        pred = reg.predict(X)\n        mape = compute_mape(pred, y)\n        regimes[\"global\"] = {\n            \"intercept\": float(reg.intercept_),\n            \"coeff_new_tokens\": float(reg.coef_[0]),\n            \"coeff_n_decode_reqs\": float(reg.coef_[1]),\n            \"mape\": mape,\n            \"n\": len(mdf),\n            \"mean_target\": float(y.mean()),\n        }\n\n        models[model_name] = regimes\n\n    return models\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 4: TTFT corrections from lifecycle data\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef estimate_ttft_corrections(data_root: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Per-model TTFT correction = observed mean TTFT from lifecycle data.\"\"\"\n    corrections = {}\n    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(data_root)):\n        dirpath = os.path.join(data_root, dirname)\n        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n            continue\n        lifecycle_path = os.path.join(\n            dirpath, \"results\", \"per_request_lifecycle_metrics.json\"\n        )\n        if not os.path.isfile(lifecycle_path):\n            continue\n\n        meta = parse_experiment_metadata(dirname)\n        model = meta[\"model\"]\n\n        try:\n            lifecycle_df = load_lifecycle_data(dirpath)\n        except Exception:\n            continue\n\n        ttft_values = []\n        for _, row in lifecycle_df.iterrows():\n            times = row.get(\"output_token_times\", [])\n            start = row.get(\"start_time\", 0)\n            if times and len(times) > 0 and start > 0:\n                ttft_s = times[0] - start\n                if ttft_s > 0:\n                    ttft_values.append(ttft_s)\n\n        if ttft_values:\n            corrections.setdefault(model, []).extend(ttft_values)\n\n    result = {}\n    for model, values in corrections.items():\n        mean_ttft_us = float(np.mean(values)) * 1_000_000\n        result[model] = mean_ttft_us\n        print(f\"  TTFT correction for {model}: {mean_ttft_us:.0f}us ({mean_ttft_us/1000:.1f}ms)\")\n\n    return result\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 5: Export StepML artifacts\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef export_stepml_artifact(\n    model_name: str, regimes: dict, ttft_correction_us: float, output_path: str\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Export per-model StepML JSON artifact.\"\"\"\n    mult = regimes.get(\"multiplier\", 2.0)\n\n    # Use decode-only intercept as overhead floor\n    if \"decode_only\" in regimes:\n        d = regimes[\"decode_only\"]\n        overhead_us = max(d[\"intercept\"], 1000)\n    elif \"global\" in regimes:\n        overhead_us = max(regimes[\"global\"][\"intercept\"], 1000)\n    else:\n        overhead_us = 4000\n\n    step_time_regimes = []\n\n    if \"decode_only\" in regimes:\n        d = regimes[\"decode_only\"]\n        step_time_regimes.append(\n            {\n                \"name\": \"decode_only\",\n                \"condition\": {\"feature\": \"prefill_tokens\", \"op\": \"==\", \"value\": 0},\n                \"model\": {\n                    \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n                    \"intercept\": d[\"intercept\"],\n                    \"feature_coefficients\": {\n                        \"decode_tokens\": d[\"coeff_new_tokens\"],\n                        \"num_decode_reqs\": d[\"coeff_n_decode_reqs\"],\n                    },\n                },\n            }\n        )\n\n    if \"mixed\" in regimes:\n        m = regimes[\"mixed\"]\n        step_time_regimes.append(\n            {\n                \"name\": \"mixed\",\n                \"condition\": None,\n                \"model\": {\n                    \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n                    \"intercept\": m[\"intercept\"],\n                    \"feature_coefficients\": {\n                        \"scheduled_tokens\": m[\"coeff_new_tokens\"],\n                        \"num_decode_reqs\": m[\"coeff_n_decode_reqs\"],\n                    },\n                },\n            }\n        )\n\n    if not step_time_regimes:\n        g = regimes[\"global\"]\n        step_time_regimes.append(\n            {\n                \"name\": \"global\",\n                \"condition\": None,\n                \"model\": {\n                    \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n                    \"intercept\": g[\"intercept\"],\n                    \"feature_coefficients\": {\n                        \"scheduled_tokens\": g[\"coeff_new_tokens\"],\n                        \"num_decode_reqs\": g[\"coeff_n_decode_reqs\"],\n                    },\n                },\n            }\n        )\n\n    artifact = {\n        \"version\": 2,\n        \"step_time_regimes\": step_time_regimes,\n        \"step_overhead_us\": overhead_us,\n        \"output_token_processing_time_us\": 0,\n        \"scheduling_processing_time_us\": 0,\n        \"preemption_processing_time_us\": 0,\n    }\n\n    if ttft_correction_us > 0:\n        artifact[\"queueing_time\"] = {\n            \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n            \"intercept\": ttft_correction_us,\n            \"feature_coefficients\": {},\n        }\n\n    with open(output_path, \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump(artifact, f, indent=2)\n\n    print(\n        f\"  {model_name}: overhead={overhead_us:.0f}us, \"\n        f\"TTFT={ttft_correction_us:.0f}us, mult={mult:.2f}x\"\n    )\n    return artifact\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 6: BLIS validation\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef run_blis_validation_per_model(\n    data_root: str, artifacts: dict, output_csv: str\n) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    \"\"\"Run BLIS validation with per-model StepML artifacts.\"\"\"\n    from validate_blis import (\n        parse_experiment_dir,\n        load_ground_truth_metrics,\n        load_exp_config,\n        extract_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log,\n        extract_cpu_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log,\n        load_profile,\n        build_workload_spec,\n        run_blis,\n        compute_error,\n    )\n    import tempfile\n    import yaml\n\n    binary = DEFAULT_BINARY\n    if not os.path.isfile(binary):\n        import subprocess\n        repo_root = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(_SHARED_DIR, \"..\", \"..\", \"..\"))\n        subprocess.run([\"go\", \"build\", \"-o\", binary, \"main.go\"], cwd=repo_root, check=True)\n\n    results = []\n    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(data_root)):\n        dirpath = os.path.join(data_root, dirname)\n        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n            continue\n        summary_path = os.path.join(dirpath, \"results\", \"summary_lifecycle_metrics.json\")\n        if not os.path.isfile(summary_path):\n            continue\n\n        try:\n            meta = parse_experiment_dir(dirname)\n        except ValueError:\n            continue\n\n        model_name = meta[\"model\"]\n\n        # Find matching artifact\n        artifact_path = None\n        for art_model, art_path in artifacts.items():\n            if art_model == model_name:\n                artifact_path = art_path\n                break\n        if artifact_path is None:\n            for art_model, art_path in artifacts.items():\n                if art_model.replace(\"-hf\", \"\") == model_name.replace(\"-hf\", \"\"):\n                    artifact_path = art_path\n                    break\n        if artifact_path is None:\n            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"no_artifact\"})\n            continue\n\n        gt = load_ground_truth_metrics(dirpath)\n        exp_config = load_exp_config(dirpath)\n        total_kv_blocks = extract_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log(dirpath)\n        cpu_kv_blocks = extract_cpu_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log(dirpath)\n\n        if total_kv_blocks is None:\n            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"no_kv_blocks\"})\n            continue\n\n        try:\n            profile = load_profile(dirpath)\n        except Exception:\n            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"no_profile\"})\n            continue\n\n        workload_spec = build_workload_spec(profile, gt)\n\n        with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(mode=\"w\", suffix=\".yaml\", delete=False) as f:\n            yaml.dump(workload_spec, f, default_flow_style=False)\n            spec_path = f.name\n\n        with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(suffix=\".json\", delete=False) as f:\n            results_json_path = f.name\n\n        try:\n            blis_metrics = run_blis(\n                binary=binary,\n                workload_spec_path=spec_path,\n                exp_config=exp_config,\n                total_kv_blocks=total_kv_blocks,\n                alpha_coeffs=[0, 0, 0],\n                beta_coeffs=[0, 0, 0],\n                results_path=results_json_path,\n                stepml_model_path=artifact_path,\n                cpu_kv_blocks=cpu_kv_blocks,\n            )\n        finally:\n            os.unlink(spec_path)\n            if os.path.exists(results_json_path):\n                os.unlink(results_json_path)\n\n        if blis_metrics is None:\n            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"blis_failed\"})\n            continue\n\n        e2e_err = compute_error(blis_metrics[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], gt[\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n        ttft_err = compute_error(blis_metrics[\"ttft_mean_ms\"], gt[\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n        itl_err = compute_error(blis_metrics[\"itl_mean_ms\"], gt[\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n\n        print(f\"  {dirname}: E2E={e2e_err*100:.1f}%, TTFT={ttft_err*100:.1f}%, ITL={itl_err*100:.1f}%\")\n\n        results.append({\n            \"experiment\": dirname,\n            \"model\": model_name,\n            \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"],\n            \"tp\": meta[\"tp\"],\n            \"status\": \"ok\",\n            \"gt_e2e_ms\": gt[\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n            \"gt_ttft_ms\": gt[\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n            \"gt_itl_ms\": gt[\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n            \"blis_e2e_ms\": blis_metrics[\"e2e_mean_ms\"],\n            \"blis_ttft_ms\": blis_metrics[\"ttft_mean_ms\"],\n            \"blis_itl_ms\": blis_metrics[\"itl_mean_ms\"],\n            \"e2e_error\": e2e_err,\n            \"ttft_error\": ttft_err,\n            \"itl_error\": itl_err,\n            \"blis_completed\": blis_metrics[\"completed_requests\"],\n            \"gt_requests\": gt[\"num_requests\"],\n        })\n\n    df = pd.DataFrame(results)\n    df.to_csv(output_csv, index=False)\n    return df\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Main\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef main():\n    print(\"=\" * 70)\n    print(\"H1: Stage 1 Principled Base — Overhead-Scaled + TTFT Corrections\")\n    print(\"=\" * 70)\n\n    data_root = DEFAULT_DATA_ROOT\n\n    # Step 1: Compute ITL from lifecycle data\n    print(\"\\n--- Step 1: Per-model ITL from lifecycle data ---\")\n    itl_data = compute_per_model_itl(data_root)\n\n    # Step 2: Load step data and compute multipliers\n    print(\"\\n--- Step 2: Compute overhead multipliers ---\")\n    step_df = load_all_experiments(data_root)\n    multipliers = compute_overhead_multipliers(step_df, itl_data)\n\n    # Step 3: Train regression on scaled step times\n    print(\"\\n--- Step 3: Train per-model regression on scaled step times ---\")\n    models = train_per_model_regression(step_df, multipliers)\n\n    with open(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"regression_results.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump(models, f, indent=2, default=str)\n\n    # Step 4: TTFT corrections\n    print(\"\\n--- Step 4: TTFT corrections ---\")\n    ttft_corrections = estimate_ttft_corrections(data_root)\n\n    # Step 5: Export artifacts\n    print(\"\\n--- Step 5: Export StepML artifacts ---\")\n    artifact_dir = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"artifacts\")\n    os.makedirs(artifact_dir, exist_ok=True)\n\n    artifacts = {}\n    for model_name, regimes in models.items():\n        ttft_us = 0\n        for ttft_model, ttft_val in ttft_corrections.items():\n            if ttft_model == model_name or ttft_model.replace(\"-hf\", \"\") == model_name.replace(\"-hf\", \"\"):\n                ttft_us = ttft_val\n                break\n\n        artifact_path = os.path.join(artifact_dir, f\"{model_name}.json\")\n        export_stepml_artifact(model_name, regimes, ttft_us, artifact_path)\n        artifacts[model_name] = artifact_path\n\n    # Step 6: BLIS validation\n    print(\"\\n--- Step 6: BLIS validation ---\")\n    results_csv = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"blis_validation.csv\")\n    results_df = run_blis_validation_per_model(data_root, artifacts, results_csv)\n\n    # Summary\n    ok = results_df[results_df[\"status\"] == \"ok\"]\n    if len(ok) > 0:\n        mean_e2e = ok[\"e2e_error\"].mean() * 100\n        mean_ttft = ok[\"ttft_error\"].mean() * 100\n        mean_itl = ok[\"itl_error\"].mean() * 100\n\n        print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\n        print(\"STAGE 1 RESULTS SUMMARY\")\n        print(\"=\" * 70)\n        print(f\"Experiments: {len(ok)}\")\n        print(f\"Mean E2E:  {mean_e2e:.1f}% (target <30%)\")\n        print(f\"Mean TTFT: {mean_ttft:.1f}%\")\n        print(f\"Mean ITL:  {mean_itl:.1f}% (target <20%)\")\n        below_10 = (ok[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.10).sum()\n        print(f\"E2E < 10%: {below_10}/{len(ok)}\")\n\n        print(f\"\\n{'Experiment':<55} {'E2E%':>7} {'TTFT%':>7} {'ITL%':>7}\")\n        print(\"-\" * 80)\n        for _, row in ok.iterrows():\n            print(\n                f\"{row['experiment']:<55} {row['e2e_error']*100:>7.1f} \"\n                f\"{row['ttft_error']*100:>7.1f} {row['itl_error']*100:>7.1f}\"\n            )\n        print(\"-\" * 80)\n        print(f\"{'MEAN':<55} {mean_e2e:>7.1f} {mean_ttft:>7.1f} {mean_itl:>7.1f}\")\n\n        # Save summary\n        summary = {\n            \"mean_e2e_error\": mean_e2e,\n            \"mean_ttft_error\": mean_ttft,\n            \"mean_itl_error\": mean_itl,\n            \"n_experiments\": len(ok),\n            \"n_below_10_e2e\": int(below_10),\n            \"per_experiment\": ok[\n                [\"experiment\", \"model\", \"workload\", \"e2e_error\", \"ttft_error\", \"itl_error\",\n                 \"gt_e2e_ms\", \"blis_e2e_ms\", \"gt_itl_ms\", \"blis_itl_ms\"]\n            ].to_dict(\"records\"),\n            \"multipliers\": multipliers,\n            \"regression_results\": {k: {rk: rv for rk, rv in v.items() if rk != \"multiplier\"} for k, v in models.items()},\n            \"ttft_corrections\": {k: float(v) for k, v in ttft_corrections.items()},\n            \"itl_data\": itl_data,\n        }\n        with open(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"h1_summary.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n            json.dump(summary, f, indent=2, default=str)\n    else:\n        print(\"\\nERROR: No experiments completed successfully!\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":11,"newStart":1,"newLines":19,"lines":[" #!/usr/bin/env python3","-\"\"\"H1: Stage 1 Principled Base — Cycle-Time Regression + TTFT Corrections.","+\"\"\"H1: Stage 1 Principled Base — Overhead-Scaled Step Time + TTFT Corrections."," ","-Extracts step cycle times from lifecycle per-token timestamps, trains per-model","-FairBatching regression (cycle_time = a + b*new_tokens + c*kv_sum), applies","-TTFT additive corrections, exports StepML artifacts, and runs BLIS validation.","+Key insight from R3: BLIS simulates a \"faster universe\" (~40% of real time).","+The root cause is that step.duration_us measures only GPU forward-pass time,","+while real step cycle time includes CPU scheduling overhead, CUDA sync, and","+memory management. The overhead floor (max(overhead, compute)) is the right","+mechanism but needs calibration from lifecycle data."," ","-This produces the \"principled base\" used by H2's constrained CMA-ES.","+This script:","+1. Computes per-model median ITL from lifecycle data (the true step cycle time)","+2. Computes per-model median step.duration_us (GPU-only time)","+3. Derives overhead_multiplier = median_ITL / median_duration (typically ~2-3x)","+4. Trains per-model regime regression on SCALED step times (duration * multiplier)","+5. Applies TTFT additive corrections from lifecycle data","+6. Exports StepML artifacts and runs BLIS validation"," \"\"\""," "," import json"]},{"oldStart":22,"oldLines":275,"newStart":30,"newLines":259,"lines":[" _SHARED_DIR = os.path.join(_IDEA_DIR, \"..\", \"..\", \"shared\")"," sys.path.insert(0, _SHARED_DIR)"," ","-from data_loader import load_all_experiments, load_lifecycle_data, parse_experiment_metadata, DEFAULT_DATA_ROOT","-from evaluation import compute_mape","-from validate_blis import (","-    validate_all_experiments,","-    DEFAULT_BINARY,","+from data_loader import (","+    load_all_experiments,","+    load_lifecycle_data,","+    parse_experiment_metadata,","+    DEFAULT_DATA_ROOT,"," )","+from evaluation import compute_mape","+from validate_blis import DEFAULT_BINARY"," "," OUTPUT_DIR = os.path.join(_SCRIPT_DIR, \"output\")"," os.makedirs(OUTPUT_DIR, exist_ok=True)"," ","+"," # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------","-# Step 1: Extract cycle times from lifecycle data","+# Step 1: Compute per-model ITL from lifecycle data"," # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------","+def compute_per_model_itl(data_root: str) -> dict:","+    \"\"\"Compute per-model median inter-token latency from lifecycle data."," ","-def extract_cycle_times_for_experiment(experiment_dir: str) -> pd.DataFrame:","-    \"\"\"Extract per-step cycle times from lifecycle per-token timestamps.","+    ITL = median of (output_token_times[i+1] - output_token_times[i]) for all","+    requests in all experiments for each model. This is the true step cycle time","+    as seen by the client (GPU compute + CPU overhead + CUDA sync).","+    \"\"\"","+    model_itls = {}  # {model: [itl_values]}"," ","-    Cycle time = inter-token interval (ITI) = time between consecutive","-    output token emissions across ALL requests in a step. This measures","-    the actual wall-clock step period, including CPU overhead.","+    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(data_root)):","+        dirpath = os.path.join(data_root, dirname)","+        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):","+            continue","+        lifecycle_path = os.path.join(","+            dirpath, \"results\", \"per_request_lifecycle_metrics.json\"","+        )","+        if not os.path.isfile(lifecycle_path):","+            continue"," ","-    Returns DataFrame with columns: step_idx, cycle_time_us, n_tokens","-    \"\"\"","-    lifecycle_df = load_lifecycle_data(experiment_dir)","+        meta = parse_experiment_metadata(dirname)","+        model = meta[\"model\"]"," ","-    # Collect all output token timestamps with their request IDs","-    all_token_events = []","-    for req_id, row in lifecycle_df.iterrows():","-        times = row[\"output_token_times\"]","-        if not times or len(times) < 2:","+        try:","+            lifecycle_df = load_lifecycle_data(dirpath)","+        except Exception:","             continue","-        for i in range(1, len(times)):","-            iti_s = times[i] - times[i-1]","-            iti_us = iti_s * 1_000_000","-            all_token_events.append({","-                \"request_id\": req_id,","-                \"token_idx\": i,","-                \"iti_us\": iti_us,","-                \"timestamp\": times[i],","-            })"," ","-    if not all_token_events:","-        return pd.DataFrame()","+        itls = []","+        for _, row in lifecycle_df.iterrows():","+            times = row.get(\"output_token_times\", [])","+            if not times or len(times) < 2:","+                continue","+            for i in range(1, len(times)):","+                iti_s = times[i] - times[i - 1]","+                if iti_s > 0:","+                    itls.append(iti_s * 1_000_000)  # convert to us"," ","-    df = pd.DataFrame(all_token_events)","+        if itls:","+            model_itls.setdefault(model, []).extend(itls)"," ","-    # Group by approximate step window (tokens emitted in same step","-    # have similar timestamps). Use binning by median ITI.","-    median_iti = df[\"iti_us\"].median()","+    result = {}","+    for model, itls in model_itls.items():","+        arr = np.array(itls)","+        result[model] = {","+            \"median_itl_us\": float(np.median(arr)),","+            \"mean_itl_us\": float(np.mean(arr)),","+            \"p10_itl_us\": float(np.percentile(arr, 10)),","+            \"p90_itl_us\": float(np.percentile(arr, 90)),","+            \"n_tokens\": len(arr),","+        }","+        print(","+            f\"  {model}: median_ITL={result[model]['median_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"","+            f\"mean_ITL={result[model]['mean_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"","+            f\"p10={result[model]['p10_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"","+            f\"p90={result[model]['p90_itl_us']:.0f}us, n={len(arr)}\"","+        )"," ","-    # Return per-token ITI data - we'll aggregate at the step level later","-    return df","+    return result"," "," ","-def extract_step_level_cycle_times(experiment_dir: str, step_df: pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame:","-    \"\"\"Match lifecycle ITI data with step-level traces to get per-step cycle times.","+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------","+# Step 2: Compute overhead multiplier per model","+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------","+def compute_overhead_multipliers(","+    step_df: pd.DataFrame, itl_data: dict","+) -> dict:","+    \"\"\"Compute per-model overhead multiplier = median_ITL / median_step_duration."," ","-    Strategy: For each step, the cycle time is the wall-clock time between","-    consecutive step starts (step N+1 start - step N start), computed from","-    step.ts_start_ns. This is simpler and more reliable than ITI matching.","+    This captures the ratio of real cycle time (ITL) to GPU-only time (duration).","     \"\"\"","-    if \"step.ts_start_ns\" not in step_df.columns:","-        return pd.DataFrame()","+    multipliers = {}","+    for model in sorted(step_df[\"model\"].unique()):","+        mdf = step_df[step_df[\"model\"] == model]","+        dur = mdf[\"step.duration_us\"].dropna()","+        if len(dur) == 0:","+            continue"," ","-    sorted_steps = step_df.sort_values(\"step.id\").copy()","-    sorted_steps = sorted_steps.dropna(subset=[\"step.ts_start_ns\"])","+        median_dur = float(dur.median())","+        itl_info = itl_data.get(model)","+        if itl_info is None:","+            # Try normalized name","+            for k, v in itl_data.items():","+                if k.replace(\"-hf\", \"\") == model.replace(\"-hf\", \"\"):","+                    itl_info = v","+                    break"," ","-    if len(sorted_steps) < 2:","-        return pd.DataFrame()","+        if itl_info is None:","+            print(f\"  {model}: no ITL data, using 2.0x default multiplier\")","+            multipliers[model] = {","+                \"multiplier\": 2.0,","+                \"median_dur_us\": median_dur,","+                \"median_itl_us\": median_dur * 2.0,","+            }","+            continue"," ","-    # Cycle time = difference between consecutive step start timestamps","-    ts_start = sorted_steps[\"step.ts_start_ns\"].values.astype(np.float64)","-    cycle_times_ns = np.diff(ts_start)","-    cycle_times_us = cycle_times_ns / 1000.0","+        median_itl = itl_info[\"median_itl_us\"]","+        mult = median_itl / median_dur if median_dur > 0 else 2.0"," ","-    # The cycle time for step i is ts_start[i+1] - ts_start[i]","-    result = sorted_steps.iloc[:-1].copy()","-    result[\"cycle_time_us\"] = cycle_times_us","+        # Clamp to reasonable range [1.2, 10.0]","+        mult = max(1.2, min(10.0, mult))"," ","-    # Filter out implausible cycle times (< 100us or > 100ms)","-    mask = (result[\"cycle_time_us\"] > 100) & (result[\"cycle_time_us\"] < 100_000)","-    result = result[mask]","+        multipliers[model] = {","+            \"multiplier\": float(mult),","+            \"median_dur_us\": float(median_dur),","+            \"median_itl_us\": float(median_itl),","+        }","+        print(","+            f\"  {model}: multiplier={mult:.2f}x \"","+            f\"(median_ITL={median_itl:.0f}us / median_dur={median_dur:.0f}us)\"","+        )"," ","-    return result","+    return multipliers"," "," ","-def extract_all_cycle_times(data_root: str) -> pd.DataFrame:","-    \"\"\"Extract cycle times across all experiments.\"\"\"","-    step_df = load_all_experiments(data_root)","-","-    frames = []","-    for exp_id in step_df[\"experiment_id\"].unique():","-        exp_steps = step_df[step_df[\"experiment_id\"] == exp_id].copy()","-        exp_dir = os.path.join(data_root, exp_id)","-","-        ct_df = extract_step_level_cycle_times(exp_dir, exp_steps)","-        if len(ct_df) > 0:","-            frames.append(ct_df)","-","-    if not frames:","-        raise RuntimeError(\"No cycle times extracted from any experiment\")","-","-    result = pd.concat(frames, ignore_index=True)","-    print(f\"Extracted {len(result)} step cycle times from {len(frames)} experiments\")","-    return result","-","-"," # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------","-# Step 2: Train per-model FairBatching regression on cycle times","+# Step 3: Train per-model regression on overhead-scaled step times"," # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------","+def train_per_model_regression(","+    step_df: pd.DataFrame, multipliers: dict","+) -> dict:","+    \"\"\"Train per-model regime regression on overhead-scaled step times."," ","-def train_per_model_regression(ct_df: pd.DataFrame) -> dict:","-    \"\"\"Train per-model FairBatching-style regression on cycle times.","+    target = step.duration_us * overhead_multiplier (the estimated cycle time)","+    features = [scheduled_tokens, num_decode_reqs]","+    \"\"\"","+    models = {}"," ","-    Model: cycle_time = intercept + b1*new_tokens + b2*kv_sum","-    where new_tokens = prefill_tokens + decode_tokens (scheduled_tokens).","+    for model_name in sorted(step_df[\"model\"].unique()):","+        mdf = step_df[step_df[\"model\"] == model_name].copy()","+        mult_info = multipliers.get(model_name, {\"multiplier\": 2.0})","+        mult = mult_info[\"multiplier\"]"," ","-    Also trains regime-separated models (decode-only vs mixed).","+        # Compute scaled target","+        mdf = mdf.dropna(subset=[\"step.duration_us\"])","+        mdf[\"scaled_duration_us\"] = mdf[\"step.duration_us\"].astype(float) * mult"," ","-    Returns dict of {model_name: {regime: {intercept, coefficients, metrics}}}","-    \"\"\"","-    # Compute new_tokens feature","-    ct_df = ct_df.copy()","-    if \"batch.scheduled_tokens\" in ct_df.columns:","-        ct_df[\"new_tokens\"] = ct_df[\"batch.scheduled_tokens\"].astype(float)","-    else:","-        ct_df[\"new_to