{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014xEHi7eXTUuShxUsCawdaJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# HYPOTHESIS: Two-Stage Calibration — Principled Cycle-Time Base + Constrained CMA-ES Residual\n     2→\n     3→**Round:** 4\n     4→**Idea:** 3 — Hybrid Calibration\n     5→**Date:** 2026-03-02\n     6→**Status:** Pending\n     7→\n     8→## Context and Prior Findings\n     9→\n    10→Round 3 demonstrated two complementary results:\n    11→1. **CMA-ES** achieves 15.1% mean E2E but 87.4% ITL (E2E-focused, ITL-blind)\n    12→2. **Trace replay baseline** achieves 56.2% mean E2E but 9.5% ITL (correctly calibrated per-step but poor E2E)\n    13→\n    14→The gap exists because CMA-ES compensates for a poorly calibrated base model by distorting secondary coefficients (`output_token_processing_time_us` inflated to 1,899μs). If the base model already produces correct step cycle times (via Idea 2's cycle-time regression), CMA-ES only needs small residual adjustments — the E2E ↔ ITL tradeoff softens because there's less to compensate for.\n    15→\n    16→This idea chains Idea 2 (principled base) → Idea 1 (constrained CMA-ES) with tight bounds (±20% of base values).\n    17→\n    18→### Related Work\n    19→\n    20→- Kennedy & O'Hagan, 2001 — Bayesian calibration with discrepancy term (physics model + statistical residual)\n    21→- Revati [2025] — extends Vidur's analytical models with profiling, <5% error\n    22→- R3 Idea 3 — unconstrained CMA-ES achieving 15.1% E2E / 87.4% ITL\n    23→- R3 Finding: CMA-ES cross-model transfer achieves 14.8% LOMO E2E — transferable dynamics\n    24→\n    25→## Sub-Hypotheses\n    26→\n    27→### H1: Stage 1 Principled Base (Cycle-Time Regression + TTFT Corrections)\n    28→\n    29→**Claim:** Cycle-time regression (from Idea 2) combined with TTFT additive corrections produces a base model with **mean E2E < 30%** and **mean ITL < 20%** across 10 experiments.\n    30→\n    31→**Refutation criteria:** Mean E2E > 50% (worse than R3 trace replay baseline) OR mean ITL > 30%.\n    32→\n    33→**Method:**\n    34→1. Use Idea 2's cycle-time extraction (H1) and regression (H2) artifacts\n    35→2. Apply per-model TTFT additive corrections from R3 H3 (16–61ms) to QueueingTime\n    36→3. Set `output_token_processing_time_us = 0` (absorbed into cycle time model)\n    37→4. Run BLIS validation via trace replay\n    38→5. Report per-experiment E2E, TTFT, ITL errors\n    39→6. This is the \"principled base\" — the starting point for Stage 2\n    40→\n    41→**Note:** If Idea 2 H2 already reports BLIS E2E results, H1 here simply adds TTFT corrections. The key test is whether TTFT corrections + cycle-time base together produce a balanced model.\n    42→\n    43→**Data split:** Same as Idea 2 H2 (temporal split for regression). BLIS E2E on all experiments.\n    44→\n    45→### H2: Stage 2 Constrained CMA-ES Residual Tuning\n    46→\n    47→**Claim:** Constrained CMA-ES (±20% bounds around Stage 1 values, dual-objective E2E+ITL) improves the principled base to **mean E2E < 12%** and **mean ITL < 18%**, with at least **6/10 experiments below 10% E2E**.\n    48→\n    49→**Refutation criteria:** Mean E2E > Stage 1 E2E + 5pp (CMA-ES makes base model worse) OR mean ITL > 25%.\n    50→\n    51→**Method:**\n    52→1. Start from H1's principled base coefficients as CMA-ES initial vector\n    53→2. **Tight bounds:**\n    54→   - `step_overhead_us ∈ [base × 0.85, base × 1.15]`\n    55→   - `output_token_processing_time_us ∈ [0, 200]`\n    56→   - `scheduling_processing_time_us ∈ [0, 1000]`\n    57→   - Step-time regime coefficients ∈ [base × 0.8, base × 1.2]\n    58→3. **Dual objective:** `f(x) = 0.5 * mean_e2e + 0.5 * mean_itl + 5.0 * max(0, itl - 0.20)`\n    59→4. Per-model optimization, σ₀ = 0.05 (smaller than Idea 1's 0.1 — tighter search)\n    60→5. Max 80 evaluations per model (vs 96-152 in R3 — starting closer to optimum)\n    61→6. **Safety net:** If any model's ITL worsens by >5pp vs Stage 1, discard CMA-ES for that model and use Stage 1 directly\n    62→\n    63→### H3: LOMO Generalization (Cross-Model Transfer)\n    64→\n    65→**Claim:** The hybrid approach achieves **mean best-donor E2E < 20%** in LOMO cross-model transfer, with **mean best-donor ITL < 30%** (R3 did not report LOMO ITL).\n    66→\n    67→**Refutation criteria:** Mean best-donor E2E > 30% (2× worse than R3's 14.8%).\n    68→\n    69→**Method:**\n    70→1. For Stage 1 LOMO: Train cycle-time regression on 3 models, evaluate BLIS E2E/ITL on held-out 4th\n    71→2. For Stage 2 LOMO: Apply CMA-ES artifacts (optimized on 3 models) to held-out 4th\n    72→3. Build cross-model transfer matrix for both E2E and ITL (extends R3 H5)\n    73→4. Use `hypotheses/h-stepml/shared/splits.py:leave_one_model_out()` for splitting\n    74→5. Report which stage contributes most to generalization: principled base (Stage 1) or CMA-ES residuals (Stage 2)\n    75→\n    76→### H4: LOWO Generalization (Cross-Workload Stability)\n    77→\n    78→**Claim:** The hybrid approach shows per-model workload variance **≤ 20pp** for dense models and **mean E2E within 2× of aggregate** for all 10 experiments.\n    79→\n    80→**Refutation criteria:** More than 3/10 experiments exceed 2× aggregate E2E.\n    81→\n    82→**Method:**\n    83→1. Evaluate per-experiment E2E/ITL from H2's best configuration\n    84→2. Group by model, compute per-workload breakdown\n    85→3. Measure range (max-min) per model\n    86→4. Compare against R3 LOWO results (8/10 within 2×)\n    87→5. Use `hypotheses/h-stepml/shared/splits.py:leave_one_workload_out()` for data splitting\n    88→\n    89→## Execution Plan\n    90→\n    91→1. **Depends on Idea 2 H1+H2:** Stage 1 uses Idea 2's cycle-time regression artifacts. If Idea 2 is executed first, Stage 1 reuses those artifacts; if not, Stage 1 re-derives them.\n    92→2. H1 — evaluate Stage 1 (principled base + TTFT corrections)\n    93→3. H2 — run Stage 2 CMA-ES on top of Stage 1\n    94→4. H3 + H4 — LOMO/LOWO generalization (can run in parallel after H2)\n    95→\n    96→## Short-Circuit Criteria\n    97→\n    98→- If Idea 2 H1 fails (cannot extract cycle times), this idea is blocked. Fall back to using R3's regime ensemble as the Stage 1 base.\n    99→- If H1 (Stage 1) produces mean E2E > 50% AND mean ITL > 25%, the principled base is not better than R3's trace replay — skip Stage 2 and document why.\n   100→- If H2 (Stage 2) produces E2E > 18% AND ITL > 25% (worse than both Idea 1 and R3 on both metrics), the hybrid approach is not synergistic — abort H3/H4.\n   101→\n   102→## Expected Outcome\n   103→\n   104→This idea represents the highest probability of achieving the research target: **E2E < 10% AND ITL < 15%**. By combining a correctly calibrated base (modeling what is measured) with constrained optimization (small residual corrections), we avoid the catastrophic E2E ↔ ITL tradeoff that plagued R3.\n   105→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CfKY3CEYt1bGTQUxibMBP7","session_id":"e652145f-d03b-4eb5-bbf8-d7db257fe10a","uuid":"8b2262dc-c5e5-486e-85a9-42d3b4508b50"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VNNkxRC3uHLQmqp3hD4Bzf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→#!/usr/bin/env python3\n     2→\"\"\"H1: Stage 1 Principled Base — Overhead-Scaled Step Time + TTFT Corrections.\n     3→\n     4→Key insight from R3: BLIS simulates a \"faster universe\" (~40% of real time).\n     5→The root cause is that step.duration_us measures only GPU forward-pass time,\n     6→while real step cycle time includes CPU scheduling overhead, CUDA sync, and\n     7→memory management. The overhead floor (max(overhead, compute)) is the right\n     8→mechanism but needs calibration from lifecycle data.\n     9→\n    10→This script:\n    11→1. Computes per-model median ITL from lifecycle data (the true step cycle time)\n    12→2. Computes per-model median step.duration_us (GPU-only time)\n    13→3. Derives overhead_multiplier = median_ITL / median_duration (typically ~2-3x)\n    14→4. Trains per-model regime regression on SCALED step times (duration * multiplier)\n    15→5. Applies TTFT additive corrections from lifecycle data\n    16→6. Exports StepML artifacts and runs BLIS validation\n    17→\"\"\"\n    18→\n    19→import json\n    20→import os\n    21→import sys\n    22→\n    23→import numpy as np\n    24→import pandas as pd\n    25→from sklearn.linear_model import Ridge\n    26→\n    27→# Add shared infrastructure to path\n    28→_SCRIPT_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))\n    29→_IDEA_DIR = os.path.dirname(_SCRIPT_DIR)\n    30→_SHARED_DIR = os.path.join(_IDEA_DIR, \"..\", \"..\", \"shared\")\n    31→sys.path.insert(0, _SHARED_DIR)\n    32→\n    33→from data_loader import (\n    34→    load_all_experiments,\n    35→    load_lifecycle_data,\n    36→    parse_experiment_metadata,\n    37→    DEFAULT_DATA_ROOT,\n    38→)\n    39→from evaluation import compute_mape\n    40→from validate_blis import DEFAULT_BINARY\n    41→\n    42→OUTPUT_DIR = os.path.join(_SCRIPT_DIR, \"output\")\n    43→os.makedirs(OUTPUT_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n    44→\n    45→\n    46→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    47→# Step 1: Compute per-model ITL from lifecycle data\n    48→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    49→def compute_per_model_itl(data_root: str) -> dict:\n    50→    \"\"\"Compute per-model median inter-token latency from lifecycle data.\n    51→\n    52→    ITL = median of (output_token_times[i+1] - output_token_times[i]) for all\n    53→    requests in all experiments for each model. This is the true step cycle time\n    54→    as seen by the client (GPU compute + CPU overhead + CUDA sync).\n    55→    \"\"\"\n    56→    model_itls = {}  # {model: [itl_values]}\n    57→\n    58→    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(data_root)):\n    59→        dirpath = os.path.join(data_root, dirname)\n    60→        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n    61→            continue\n    62→        lifecycle_path = os.path.join(\n    63→            dirpath, \"results\", \"per_request_lifecycle_metrics.json\"\n    64→        )\n    65→        if not os.path.isfile(lifecycle_path):\n    66→            continue\n    67→\n    68→        meta = parse_experiment_metadata(dirname)\n    69→        model = meta[\"model\"]\n    70→\n    71→        try:\n    72→            lifecycle_df = load_lifecycle_data(dirpath)\n    73→        except Exception:\n    74→            continue\n    75→\n    76→        itls = []\n    77→        for _, row in lifecycle_df.iterrows():\n    78→            times = row.get(\"output_token_times\", [])\n    79→            if not times or len(times) < 2:\n    80→                continue\n    81→            for i in range(1, len(times)):\n    82→                iti_s = times[i] - times[i - 1]\n    83→                if iti_s > 0:\n    84→                    itls.append(iti_s * 1_000_000)  # convert to us\n    85→\n    86→        if itls:\n    87→            model_itls.setdefault(model, []).extend(itls)\n    88→\n    89→    result = {}\n    90→    for model, itls in model_itls.items():\n    91→        arr = np.array(itls)\n    92→        result[model] = {\n    93→            \"median_itl_us\": float(np.median(arr)),\n    94→            \"mean_itl_us\": float(np.mean(arr)),\n    95→            \"p10_itl_us\": float(np.percentile(arr, 10)),\n    96→            \"p90_itl_us\": float(np.percentile(arr, 90)),\n    97→            \"n_tokens\": len(arr),\n    98→        }\n    99→        print(\n   100→            f\"  {model}: median_ITL={result[model]['median_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"\n   101→            f\"mean_ITL={result[model]['mean_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"\n   102→            f\"p10={result[model]['p10_itl_us']:.0f}us, \"\n   103→            f\"p90={result[model]['p90_itl_us']:.0f}us, n={len(arr)}\"\n   104→        )\n   105→\n   106→    return result\n   107→\n   108→\n   109→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   110→# Step 2: Compute overhead multiplier per model\n   111→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   112→def compute_overhead_multipliers(\n   113→    step_df: pd.DataFrame, itl_data: dict\n   114→) -> dict:\n   115→    \"\"\"Compute per-model overhead multiplier = median_ITL / median_step_duration.\n   116→\n   117→    This captures the ratio of real cycle time (ITL) to GPU-only time (duration).\n   118→    \"\"\"\n   119→    multipliers = {}\n   120→    for model in sorted(step_df[\"model\"].unique()):\n   121→        mdf = step_df[step_df[\"model\"] == model]\n   122→        dur = mdf[\"step.duration_us\"].dropna()\n   123→        if len(dur) == 0:\n   124→            continue\n   125→\n   126→        median_dur = float(dur.median())\n   127→        itl_info = itl_data.get(model)\n   128→        if itl_info is None:\n   129→            # Try normalized name\n   130→            for k, v in itl_data.items():\n   131→                if k.replace(\"-hf\", \"\") == model.replace(\"-hf\", \"\"):\n   132→                    itl_info = v\n   133→                    break\n   134→\n   135→        if itl_info is None:\n   136→            print(f\"  {model}: no ITL data, using 2.0x default multiplier\")\n   137→            multipliers[model] = {\n   138→                \"multiplier\": 2.0,\n   139→                \"median_dur_us\": median_dur,\n   140→                \"median_itl_us\": median_dur * 2.0,\n   141→            }\n   142→            continue\n   143→\n   144→        median_itl = itl_info[\"median_itl_us\"]\n   145→        mult = median_itl / median_dur if median_dur > 0 else 2.0\n   146→\n   147→        # Clamp to reasonable range [1.2, 10.0]\n   148→        mult = max(1.2, min(10.0, mult))\n   149→\n   150→        multipliers[model] = {\n   151→            \"multiplier\": float(mult),\n   152→            \"median_dur_us\": float(median_dur),\n   153→            \"median_itl_us\": float(median_itl),\n   154→        }\n   155→        print(\n   156→            f\"  {model}: multiplier={mult:.2f}x \"\n   157→            f\"(median_ITL={median_itl:.0f}us / median_dur={median_dur:.0f}us)\"\n   158→        )\n   159→\n   160→    return multipliers\n   161→\n   162→\n   163→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   164→# Step 3: Train per-model regression on overhead-scaled step times\n   165→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   166→def train_per_model_regression(\n   167→    step_df: pd.DataFrame, multipliers: dict\n   168→) -> dict:\n   169→    \"\"\"Train per-model regime regression on overhead-scaled step times.\n   170→\n   171→    target = step.duration_us * overhead_multiplier (the estimated cycle time)\n   172→    features = [scheduled_tokens, num_decode_reqs]\n   173→    \"\"\"\n   174→    models = {}\n   175→\n   176→    for model_name in sorted(step_df[\"model\"].unique()):\n   177→        mdf = step_df[step_df[\"model\"] == model_name].copy()\n   178→        mult_info = multipliers.get(model_name, {\"multiplier\": 2.0})\n   179→        mult = mult_info[\"multiplier\"]\n   180→\n   181→        # Compute scaled target\n   182→        mdf = mdf.dropna(subset=[\"step.duration_us\"])\n   183→        mdf[\"scaled_duration_us\"] = mdf[\"step.duration_us\"].astype(float) * mult\n   184→\n   185→        # Feature columns\n   186→        if \"batch.scheduled_tokens\" in mdf.columns:\n   187→            mdf[\"new_tokens\"] = mdf[\"batch.scheduled_tokens\"].astype(float)\n   188→        else:\n   189→            mdf[\"new_tokens\"] = (\n   190→                mdf.get(\"batch.prefill_tokens\", pd.Series(0, index=mdf.index)).astype(float)\n   191→                + mdf.get(\"batch.decode_tokens\", pd.Series(0, index=mdf.index)).astype(float)\n   192→            )\n   193→\n   194→        mdf[\"n_decode_reqs\"] = mdf.get(\n   195→            \"batch.num_decode_reqs\", pd.Series(0, index=mdf.index)\n   196→        ).astype(float)\n   197→\n   198→        # Regime separation\n   199→        if \"batch.prefill_tokens\" in mdf.columns:\n   200→            decode_only = mdf[mdf[\"batch.prefill_tokens\"] == 0]\n   201→            mixed = mdf[mdf[\"batch.prefill_tokens\"] > 0]\n   202→        else:\n   203→            decode_only = mdf\n   204→            mixed = mdf.iloc[0:0]\n   205→\n   206→        regimes = {\"multiplier\": mult}\n   207→\n   208→        # Train decode-only\n   209→        if len(decode_only) >= 10:\n   210→            X = decode_only[[\"new_tokens\", \"n_decode_reqs\"]].values\n   211→            y = decode_only[\"scaled_duration_us\"].values\n   212→            reg = Ridge(alpha=10.0)\n   213→            reg.fit(X, y)\n   214→            pred = reg.predict(X)\n   215→            mape = compute_mape(pred, y)\n   216→            regimes[\"decode_only\"] = {\n   217→                \"intercept\": float(reg.intercept_),\n   218→                \"coeff_new_tokens\": float(reg.coef_[0]),\n   219→                \"coeff_n_decode_reqs\": float(reg.coef_[1]),\n   220→                \"mape\": mape,\n   221→                \"n\": len(decode_only),\n   222→                \"mean_target\": float(y.mean()),\n   223→            }\n   224→            print(\n   225→                f\"  {model_name} decode-only: intercept={reg.intercept_:.0f}, \"\n   226→                f\"b_tokens={reg.coef_[0]:.2f}, b_reqs={reg.coef_[1]:.2f}, \"\n   227→                f\"MAPE={mape:.1f}%, n={len(decode_only)}\"\n   228→            )\n   229→\n   230→        # Train mixed\n   231→        if len(mixed) >= 10:\n   232→            X = mixed[[\"new_tokens\", \"n_decode_reqs\"]].values\n   233→            y = mixed[\"scaled_duration_us\"].values\n   234→            reg = Ridge(alpha=10.0)\n   235→            reg.fit(X, y)\n   236→            pred = reg.predict(X)\n   237→            mape = compute_mape(pred, y)\n   238→            regimes[\"mixed\"] = {\n   239→                \"intercept\": float(reg.intercept_),\n   240→                \"coeff_new_tokens\": float(reg.coef_[0]),\n   241→                \"coeff_n_decode_reqs\": float(reg.coef_[1]),\n   242→                \"mape\": mape,\n   243→                \"n\": len(mixed),\n   244→                \"mean_target\": float(y.mean()),\n   245→            }\n   246→            print(\n   247→                f\"  {model_name} mixed:       intercept={reg.intercept_:.0f}, \"\n   248→                f\"b_tokens={reg.coef_[0]:.2f}, b_reqs={reg.coef_[1]:.2f}, \"\n   249→                f\"MAPE={mape:.1f}%, n={len(mixed)}\"\n   250→            )\n   251→\n   252→        # Global\n   253→        X = mdf[[\"new_tokens\", \"n_decode_reqs\"]].values\n   254→        y = mdf[\"scaled_duration_us\"].values\n   255→        reg = Ridge(alpha=10.0)\n   256→        reg.fit(X, y)\n   257→        pred = reg.predict(X)\n   258→        mape = compute_mape(pred, y)\n   259→        regimes[\"global\"] = {\n   260→            \"intercept\": float(reg.intercept_),\n   261→            \"coeff_new_tokens\": float(reg.coef_[0]),\n   262→            \"coeff_n_decode_reqs\": float(reg.coef_[1]),\n   263→            \"mape\": mape,\n   264→            \"n\": len(mdf),\n   265→            \"mean_target\": float(y.mean()),\n   266→        }\n   267→\n   268→        models[model_name] = regimes\n   269→\n   270→    return models\n   271→\n   272→\n   273→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   274→# Step 4: TTFT corrections from lifecycle data\n   275→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   276→def estimate_ttft_corrections(data_root: str) -> dict:\n   277→    \"\"\"Per-model TTFT correction = observed mean TTFT from lifecycle data.\"\"\"\n   278→    corrections = {}\n   279→    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(data_root)):\n   280→        dirpath = os.path.join(data_root, dirname)\n   281→        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n   282→            continue\n   283→        lifecycle_path = os.path.join(\n   284→            dirpath, \"results\", \"per_request_lifecycle_metrics.json\"\n   285→        )\n   286→        if not os.path.isfile(lifecycle_path):\n   287→            continue\n   288→\n   289→        meta = parse_experiment_metadata(dirname)\n   290→        model = meta[\"model\"]\n   291→\n   292→        try:\n   293→            lifecycle_df = load_lifecycle_data(dirpath)\n   294→        except Exception:\n   295→            continue\n   296→\n   297→        ttft_values = []\n   298→        for _, row in lifecycle_df.iterrows():\n   299→            times = row.get(\"output_token_times\", [])\n   300→            start = row.get(\"start_time\", 0)\n   301→            if times and len(times) > 0 and start > 0:\n   302→                ttft_s = times[0] - start\n   303→                if ttft_s > 0:\n   304→                    ttft_values.append(ttft_s)\n   305→\n   306→        if ttft_values:\n   307→            corrections.setdefault(model, []).extend(ttft_values)\n   308→\n   309→    result = {}\n   310→    for model, values in corrections.items():\n   311→        mean_ttft_us = float(np.mean(values)) * 1_000_000\n   312→        result[model] = mean_ttft_us\n   313→        print(f\"  TTFT correction for {model}: {mean_ttft_us:.0f}us ({mean_ttft_us/1000:.1f}ms)\")\n   314→\n   315→    return result\n   316→\n   317→\n   318→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   319→# Step 5: Export StepML artifacts\n   320→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   321→def export_stepml_artifact(\n   322→    model_name: str, regimes: dict, ttft_correction_us: float, output_path: str\n   323→) -> dict:\n   324→    \"\"\"Export per-model StepML JSON artifact.\"\"\"\n   325→    mult = regimes.get(\"multiplier\", 2.0)\n   326→\n   327→    # Use decode-only intercept as overhead floor\n   328→    if \"decode_only\" in regimes:\n   329→        d = regimes[\"decode_only\"]\n   330→        overhead_us = max(d[\"intercept\"], 1000)\n   331→    elif \"global\" in regimes:\n   332→        overhead_us = max(regimes[\"global\"][\"intercept\"], 1000)\n   333→    else:\n   334→        overhead_us = 4000\n   335→\n   336→    step_time_regimes = []\n   337→\n   338→    if \"decode_only\" in regimes:\n   339→        d = regimes[\"decode_only\"]\n   340→        step_time_regimes.append(\n   341→            {\n   342→                \"name\": \"decode_only\",\n   343→                \"condition\": {\"feature\": \"prefill_tokens\", \"op\": \"==\", \"value\": 0},\n   344→                \"model\": {\n   345→                    \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n   346→                    \"intercept\": d[\"intercept\"],\n   347→                    \"feature_coefficients\": {\n   348→                        \"decode_tokens\": d[\"coeff_new_tokens\"],\n   349→                        \"num_decode_reqs\": d[\"coeff_n_decode_reqs\"],\n   350→                    },\n   351→                },\n   352→            }\n   353→        )\n   354→\n   355→    if \"mixed\" in regimes:\n   356→        m = regimes[\"mixed\"]\n   357→        step_time_regimes.append(\n   358→            {\n   359→                \"name\": \"mixed\",\n   360→                \"condition\": None,\n   361→                \"model\": {\n   362→                    \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n   363→                    \"intercept\": m[\"intercept\"],\n   364→                    \"feature_coefficients\": {\n   365→                        \"scheduled_tokens\": m[\"coeff_new_tokens\"],\n   366→                        \"num_decode_reqs\": m[\"coeff_n_decode_reqs\"],\n   367→                    },\n   368→                },\n   369→            }\n   370→        )\n   371→\n   372→    if not step_time_regimes:\n   373→        g = regimes[\"global\"]\n   374→        step_time_regimes.append(\n   375→            {\n   376→                \"name\": \"global\",\n   377→                \"condition\": None,\n   378→                \"model\": {\n   379→                    \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n   380→                    \"intercept\": g[\"intercept\"],\n   381→                    \"feature_coefficients\": {\n   382→                        \"scheduled_tokens\": g[\"coeff_new_tokens\"],\n   383→                        \"num_decode_reqs\": g[\"coeff_n_decode_reqs\"],\n   384→                    },\n   385→                },\n   386→            }\n   387→        )\n   388→\n   389→    artifact = {\n   390→        \"version\": 2,\n   391→        \"step_time_regimes\": step_time_regimes,\n   392→        \"step_overhead_us\": overhead_us,\n   393→        \"output_token_processing_time_us\": 0,\n   394→        \"scheduling_processing_time_us\": 0,\n   395→        \"preemption_processing_time_us\": 0,\n   396→    }\n   397→\n   398→    if ttft_correction_us > 0:\n   399→        artifact[\"queueing_time\"] = {\n   400→            \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n   401→            \"intercept\": ttft_correction_us,\n   402→            \"feature_coefficients\": {},\n   403→        }\n   404→\n   405→    with open(output_path, \"w\") as f:\n   406→        json.dump(artifact, f, indent=2)\n   407→\n   408→    print(\n   409→        f\"  {model_name}: overhead={overhead_us:.0f}us, \"\n   410→        f\"TTFT={ttft_correction_us:.0f}us, mult={mult:.2f}x\"\n   411→    )\n   412→    return artifact\n   413→\n   414→\n   415→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   416→# Step 6: BLIS validation\n   417→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   418→def run_blis_validation_per_model(\n   419→    data_root: str, artifacts: dict, output_csv: str\n   420→) -> pd.DataFrame:\n   421→    \"\"\"Run BLIS validation with per-model StepML artifacts.\"\"\"\n   422→    from validate_blis import (\n   423→        parse_experiment_dir,\n   424→        load_ground_truth_metrics,\n   425→        load_exp_config,\n   426→        extract_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log,\n   427→        extract_cpu_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log,\n   428→        load_profile,\n   429→        build_workload_spec,\n   430→        run_blis,\n   431→        compute_error,\n   432→    )\n   433→    import tempfile\n   434→    import yaml\n   435→\n   436→    binary = DEFAULT_BINARY\n   437→    if not os.path.isfile(binary):\n   438→        import subprocess\n   439→        repo_root = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(_SHARED_DIR, \"..\", \"..\", \"..\"))\n   440→        subprocess.run([\"go\", \"build\", \"-o\", binary, \"main.go\"], cwd=repo_root, check=True)\n   441→\n   442→    results = []\n   443→    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(data_root)):\n   444→        dirpath = os.path.join(data_root, dirname)\n   445→        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n   446→            continue\n   447→        summary_path = os.path.join(dirpath, \"results\", \"summary_lifecycle_metrics.json\")\n   448→        if not os.path.isfile(summary_path):\n   449→            continue\n   450→\n   451→        try:\n   452→            meta = parse_experiment_dir(dirname)\n   453→        except ValueError:\n   454→            continue\n   455→\n   456→        model_name = meta[\"model\"]\n   457→\n   458→        # Find matching artifact\n   459→        artifact_path = None\n   460→        for art_model, art_path in artifacts.items():\n   461→            if art_model == model_name:\n   462→                artifact_path = art_path\n   463→                break\n   464→        if artifact_path is None:\n   465→            for art_model, art_path in artifacts.items():\n   466→                if art_model.replace(\"-hf\", \"\") == model_name.replace(\"-hf\", \"\"):\n   467→                    artifact_path = art_path\n   468→                    break\n   469→        if artifact_path is None:\n   470→            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"no_artifact\"})\n   471→            continue\n   472→\n   473→        gt = load_ground_truth_metrics(dirpath)\n   474→        exp_config = load_exp_config(dirpath)\n   475→        total_kv_blocks = extract_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log(dirpath)\n   476→        cpu_kv_blocks = extract_cpu_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log(dirpath)\n   477→\n   478→        if total_kv_blocks is None:\n   479→            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"no_kv_blocks\"})\n   480→            continue\n   481→\n   482→        try:\n   483→            profile = load_profile(dirpath)\n   484→        except Exception:\n   485→            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"no_profile\"})\n   486→            continue\n   487→\n   488→        workload_spec = build_workload_spec(profile, gt)\n   489→\n   490→        with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(mode=\"w\", suffix=\".yaml\", delete=False) as f:\n   491→            yaml.dump(workload_spec, f, default_flow_style=False)\n   492→            spec_path = f.name\n   493→\n   494→        with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(suffix=\".json\", delete=False) as f:\n   495→            results_json_path = f.name\n   496→\n   497→        try:\n   498→            blis_metrics = run_blis(\n   499→                binary=binary,\n   500→                workload_spec_path=spec_path,\n   501→                exp_config=exp_config,\n   502→                total_kv_blocks=total_kv_blocks,\n   503→                alpha_coeffs=[0, 0, 0],\n   504→                beta_coeffs=[0, 0, 0],\n   505→                results_path=results_json_path,\n   506→                stepml_model_path=artifact_path,\n   507→                cpu_kv_blocks=cpu_kv_blocks,\n   508→            )\n   509→        finally:\n   510→            os.unlink(spec_path)\n   511→            if os.path.exists(results_json_path):\n   512→                os.unlink(results_json_path)\n   513→\n   514→        if blis_metrics is None:\n   515→            results.append({\"experiment\": dirname, \"model\": model_name, \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"], \"status\": \"blis_failed\"})\n   516→            continue\n   517→\n   518→        e2e_err = compute_error(blis_metrics[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], gt[\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   519→        ttft_err = compute_error(blis_metrics[\"ttft_mean_ms\"], gt[\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   520→        itl_err = compute_error(blis_metrics[\"itl_mean_ms\"], gt[\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   521→\n   522→        print(f\"  {dirname}: E2E={e2e_err*100:.1f}%, TTFT={ttft_err*100:.1f}%, ITL={itl_err*100:.1f}%\")\n   523→\n   524→        results.append({\n   525→            \"experiment\": dirname,\n   526→            \"model\": model_name,\n   527→            \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"],\n   528→            \"tp\": meta[\"tp\"],\n   529→            \"status\": \"ok\",\n   530→            \"gt_e2e_ms\": gt[\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   531→            \"gt_ttft_ms\": gt[\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   532→            \"gt_itl_ms\": gt[\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   533→            \"blis_e2e_ms\": blis_metrics[\"e2e_mean_ms\"],\n   534→            \"blis_ttft_ms\": blis_metrics[\"ttft_mean_ms\"],\n   535→            \"blis_itl_ms\": blis_metrics[\"itl_mean_ms\"],\n   536→            \"e2e_error\": e2e_err,\n   537→            \"ttft_error\": ttft_err,\n   538→            \"itl_error\": itl_err,\n   539→            \"blis_completed\": blis_metrics[\"completed_requests\"],\n   540→            \"gt_requests\": gt[\"num_requests\"],\n   541→        })\n   542→\n   543→    df = pd.DataFrame(results)\n   544→    df.to_csv(output_csv, index=False)\n   545→    return df\n   546→\n   547→\n   548→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   549→# Main\n   550→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   551→def main():\n   552→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n   553→    print(\"H1: Stage 1 Principled Base — Overhead-Scaled + TTFT Corrections\")\n   554→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n   555→\n   556→    data_root = DEFAULT_DATA_ROOT\n   557→\n   558→    # Step 1: Compute ITL from lifecycle data\n   559→    print(\"\\n--- Step 1: Per-model ITL from lifecycle data ---\")\n   560→    itl_data = compute_per_model_itl(data_root)\n   561→\n   562→    # Step 2: Load step data and compute multipliers\n   563→    print(\"\\n--- Step 2: Compute overhead multipliers ---\")\n   564→    step_df = load_all_experiments(data_root)\n   565→    multipliers = compute_overhead_multipliers(step_df, itl_data)\n   566→\n   567→    # Step 3: Train regression on scaled step times\n   568→    print(\"\\n--- Step 3: Train per-model regression on scaled step times ---\")\n   569→    models = train_per_model_regression(step_df, multipliers)\n   570→\n   571→    with open(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"regression_results.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n   572→        json.dump(models, f, indent=2, default=str)\n   573→\n   574→    # Step 4: TTFT corrections\n   575→    print(\"\\n--- Step 4: TTFT corrections ---\")\n   576→    ttft_corrections = estimate_ttft_corrections(data_root)\n   577→\n   578→    # Step 5: Export artifacts\n   579→    print(\"\\n--- Step 5: Export StepML artifacts ---\")\n   580→    artifact_dir = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"artifacts\")\n   581→    os.makedirs(artifact_dir, exist_ok=True)\n   582→\n   583→    artifacts = {}\n   584→    for model_name, regimes in models.items():\n   585→        ttft_us = 0\n   586→        for ttft_model, ttft_val in ttft_corrections.items():\n   587→            if ttft_model == model_name or ttft_model.replace(\"-hf\", \"\") == model_name.replace(\"-hf\", \"\"):\n   588→                ttft_us = ttft_val\n   589→                break\n   590→\n   591→        artifact_path = os.path.join(artifact_dir, f\"{model_name}.json\")\n   592→        export_stepml_artifact(model_name, regimes, ttft_us, artifact_path)\n   593→        artifacts[model_name] = artifact_path\n   594→\n   595→    # Step 6: BLIS validation\n   596→    print(\"\\n--- Step 6: BLIS validation ---\")\n   597→    results_csv = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"blis_validation.csv\")\n   598→    results_df = run_blis_validation_per_model(data_root, artifacts, results_csv)\n   599→\n   600→    # Summary\n   601→    ok = results_df[results_df[\"status\"] == \"ok\"]\n   602→    if len(ok) > 0:\n   603→        mean_e2e = ok[\"e2e_error\"].mean() * 100\n   604→        mean_ttft = ok[\"ttft_error\"].mean() * 100\n   605→        mean_itl = ok[\"itl_error\"].mean() * 100\n   606→\n   607→        print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\n   608→        print(\"STAGE 1 RESULTS SUMMARY\")\n   609→        print(\"=\" * 70)\n   610→        print(f\"Experiments: {len(ok)}\")\n   611→        print(f\"Mean E2E:  {mean_e2e:.1f}% (target <30%)\")\n   612→        print(f\"Mean TTFT: {mean_ttft:.1f}%\")\n   613→        print(f\"Mean ITL:  {mean_itl:.1f}% (target <20%)\")\n   614→        below_10 = (ok[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.10).sum()\n   615→        print(f\"E2E < 10%: {below_10}/{len(ok)}\")\n   616→\n   617→        print(f\"\\n{'Experiment':<55} {'E2E%':>7} {'TTFT%':>7} {'ITL%':>7}\")\n   618→        print(\"-\" * 80)\n   619→        for _, row in ok.iterrows():\n   620→            print(\n   621→                f\"{row['experiment']:<55} {row['e2e_error']*100:>7.1f} \"\n   622→                f\"{row['ttft_error']*100:>7.1f} {row['itl_error']*100:>7.1f}\"\n   623→            )\n   624→        print(\"-\" * 80)\n   625→        print(f\"{'MEAN':<55} {mean_e2e:>7.1f} {mean_ttft:>7.1f} {mean_itl:>7.1f}\")\n   626→\n   627→        # Save summary\n   628→        summary = {\n   629→            \"mean_e2e_error\": mean_e2e,\n   630→            \"mean_ttft_error\": mean_ttft,\n   631→            \"mean_itl_error\": mean_itl,\n   632→            \"n_experiments\": len(ok),\n   633→            \"n_below_10_e2e\": int(below_10),\n   634→            \"per_experiment\": ok[\n   635→                [\"experiment\", \"model\", \"workload\", \"e2e_error\", \"ttft_error\", \"itl_error\",\n   636→                 \"gt_e2e_ms\", \"blis_e2e_ms\", \"gt_itl_ms\", \"blis_itl_ms\"]\n   637→            ].to_dict(\"records\"),\n   638→            \"multipliers\": multipliers,\n   639→            \"regression_results\": {k: {rk: rv for rk, rv in v.items() if rk != \"multiplier\"} for k, v in models.items()},\n   640→            \"ttft_corrections\": {k: float(v) for k, v in ttft_corrections.items()},\n   641→            \"itl_data\": itl_data,\n   642→        }\n   643→        with open(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"h1_summary.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n   644→            json.dump(summary, f, indent=2, default=str)\n   645→    else:\n   646→        print(\"\\nERROR: No experiments completed successfully!\")\n   647→        sys.exit(1)\n   648→\n   649→\n   650→if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n   651→    main()\n   652→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CfKY3CEYt1bGTQUxibMBP7","session_id":"e652145f-d03b-4eb5-bbf8-d7d