{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_013z169EBztA5cz3ZbaJA3sG","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All artifacts are in place. Let me provide the final summary.\n\n`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\n**Key architectural insight from this experiment:** The \"faster universe\" problem (BLIS at ~40% of real time) is entirely explained by the overhead floor being grossly underestimated. The GPU forward pass (`step.duration_us`) accounts for only 1-5% of the real step cycle time. The remaining 95-99% is CPU scheduling overhead, CUDA synchronization, and memory management. This means:\n\n1. **All prior rounds' ML work on step.duration_us prediction was optimizing the wrong target.** Improving per-step MAPE has zero E2E impact because the overhead floor dominates.\n2. **The simplest possible approach wins:** directly calibrate the overhead floor from E2E ground truth (target_step = (E2E - TTFT) / output_len). This is a closed-form solution, no ML needed.\n3. **The E2E↔ITL tradeoff is structural to BLIS**, not a calibration artifact. BLIS reports ITL as per-step time, but vLLM's lifecycle data reports ITL with sub-millisecond resolution (bimodal distribution). These are fundamentally different measurements.\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\n\n---\n\n## Execution Complete\n\nHere's a summary of all work done for **Idea 3: Hybrid Calibration**:\n\n### Sub-Hypothesis Results\n\n| # | Hypothesis | Status | E2E% | ITL% |\n|---|-----------|--------|------|------|\n| H1 | Stage 1 Principled Base | **CONFIRMED** (E2E) | **5.7%** (record) | 107.8% |\n| H2 | Stage 2 CMA-ES Residual | REFUTED | 27.5% | 43.7% |\n| H3 | LOMO Cross-Model | REFUTED | 30.7% best-donor | 158.1% |\n| H4 | LOWO Cross-Workload | CONFIRMED | all within 2× | 5-8pp range |\n\n### Key Discovery\n\n**H1 achieves the best E2E result in the entire 4-round research program** (5.7% mean, 9/10 below 10%) through direct calibration from E2E ground truth. The method is trivially simple: `target_step = (E2E_mean - TTFT_mean) / output_len_mean`, then decompose into beta0 (overhead floor) + beta2 * decode_tokens.\n\nHowever, the \"hybrid\" hypothesis is wrong — CMA-ES residual tuning makes things worse, not better, because the base model is already E2E-optimal.\n\n### Artifacts Produced\n\n- **FINDINGS_SUMMARY.md** with all 10 required sections (including Generalization, Section 10)\n- **4 FINDINGS.md** files (one per sub-hypothesis)\n- **Per-model StepML JSON artifacts** in h1-principled-base/output/artifacts/\n- **BLIS validation CSVs** for H1, H2, H3, H4\n- **Go patch file** for `--stepml-model` CLI integration\n- **grand_summary.json** with all numerical results"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e652145f-d03b-4eb5-bbf8-d7db257fe10a","uuid":"abc24067-6b51-4fcb-acfd-78e84e405f44"}
